1589 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1590 // Visitor Methods
1591 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1592 
1593 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitExpr(Expr *E) {
1594  CGF.ErrorUnsupported(E, "scalar expression");
1595  if (E->getType()->isVoidType())
1596  return nullptr;
1597  return llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.ConvertType(E->getType()));
1598 }
1599 
1600 Value *
1601 ScalarExprEmitter::VisitSYCLUniqueStableNameExpr(SYCLUniqueStableNameExpr *E) {
1602  ASTContext &Context = CGF.getContext();
1603  llvm::Optional<LangAS> GlobalAS =
1604  Context.getTargetInfo().getConstantAddressSpace();
1605  llvm::Constant *GlobalConstStr = Builder.CreateGlobalStringPtr(
1606  E->ComputeName(Context), "__usn_str",
1607  static_cast<unsigned>(GlobalAS.getValueOr(LangAS::Default)));
1608 
1609  unsigned ExprAS = Context.getTargetAddressSpace(E->getType());
1610 
1611  if (GlobalConstStr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() == ExprAS)
1612  return GlobalConstStr;
1613 
1614  llvm::PointerType *PtrTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(GlobalConstStr->getType());
1615  llvm::PointerType *NewPtrTy =
1616  llvm::PointerType::getWithSamePointeeType(PtrTy, ExprAS);
1617  return Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(GlobalConstStr, NewPtrTy, "usn_addr_cast");
1618 }
1619 
1620 Value *
1621 ScalarExprEmitter::VisitSYCLUniqueStableIdExpr(SYCLUniqueStableIdExpr *E) {
1622  ASTContext &Context = CGF.getContext();
1623  llvm::Optional<LangAS> GlobalAS =
1624  Context.getTargetInfo().getConstantAddressSpace();
1625  llvm::Constant *GlobalConstStr = Builder.CreateGlobalStringPtr(
1626  E->ComputeName(Context), "__usid_str",
1627  static_cast<unsigned>(GlobalAS.getValueOr(LangAS::Default)));
1628 
1629  unsigned ExprAS = Context.getTargetAddressSpace(E->getType());
1630 
1631  if (GlobalConstStr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() == ExprAS)
1632  return GlobalConstStr;
1633 
1634  llvm::Type *EltTy = GlobalConstStr->getType()->getPointerElementType();
1635  llvm::PointerType *NewPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(EltTy, ExprAS);
1636  return Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(GlobalConstStr, NewPtrTy,
1637  "usid_addr_cast");
1638 }
1639 
1640 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitShuffleVectorExpr(ShuffleVectorExpr *E) {
1641  // Vector Mask Case
1642  if (E->getNumSubExprs() == 2) {
1643  Value *LHS = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getExpr(0));
1644  Value *RHS = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getExpr(1));
1645  Value *Mask;
1646 
1647  auto *LTy = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(LHS->getType());
1648  unsigned LHSElts = LTy->getNumElements();
1649 
1650  Mask = RHS;
1651 
1652  auto *MTy = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(Mask->getType());
1653 
1654  // Mask off the high bits of each shuffle index.
1655  Value *MaskBits =
1656  llvm::ConstantInt::get(MTy, llvm::NextPowerOf2(LHSElts - 1) - 1);
1657  Mask = Builder.CreateAnd(Mask, MaskBits, "mask");
1658 
1659  // newv = undef
1660  // mask = mask & maskbits
1661  // for each elt
1662  // n = extract mask i
1663  // x = extract val n
1664  // newv = insert newv, x, i
1665  auto *RTy = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(LTy->getElementType(),
1666  MTy->getNumElements());
1667  Value* NewV = llvm::UndefValue::get(RTy);
1668  for (unsigned i = 0, e = MTy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
1669  Value *IIndx = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy, i);
1670  Value *Indx = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Mask, IIndx, "shuf_idx");
1671 
1672  Value *VExt = Builder.CreateExtractElement(LHS, Indx, "shuf_elt");
1673  NewV = Builder.CreateInsertElement(NewV, VExt, IIndx, "shuf_ins");
1674  }
1675  return NewV;
1676  }
1677 
1678  Value* V1 = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getExpr(0));
1679  Value* V2 = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getExpr(1));
1680 
1681  SmallVector<int, 32> Indices;
1682  for (unsigned i = 2; i < E->getNumSubExprs(); ++i) {
1683  llvm::APSInt Idx = E->getShuffleMaskIdx(CGF.getContext(), i-2);
1684  // Check for -1 and output it as undef in the IR.
1685  if (Idx.isSigned() && Idx.isAllOnes())
1686  Indices.push_back(-1);
1687  else
1688  Indices.push_back(Idx.getZExtValue());
1689  }
1690 
1691  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V1, V2, Indices, "shuffle");
1692 }
1693 
1694 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitConvertVectorExpr(ConvertVectorExpr *E) {
1695  QualType SrcType = E->getSrcExpr()->getType(),
1696  DstType = E->getType();
1697 
1698  Value *Src = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getSrcExpr());
1699 
1700  SrcType = CGF.getContext().getCanonicalType(SrcType);
1701  DstType = CGF.getContext().getCanonicalType(DstType);
1702  if (SrcType == DstType) return Src;
1703 
1704  assert(SrcType->isVectorType() &&
1705  "ConvertVector source type must be a vector");
1706  assert(DstType->isVectorType() &&
1707  "ConvertVector destination type must be a vector");
1708 
1709  llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
1710  llvm::Type *DstTy = ConvertType(DstType);
1711 
1712  // Ignore conversions like int -> uint.
1713  if (SrcTy == DstTy)
1714  return Src;
1715 
1716  QualType SrcEltType = SrcType->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType(),
1717  DstEltType = DstType->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
1718 
1719  assert(SrcTy->isVectorTy() &&
1720  "ConvertVector source IR type must be a vector");
1721  assert(DstTy->isVectorTy() &&
1722  "ConvertVector destination IR type must be a vector");
1723 
1724  llvm::Type *SrcEltTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(SrcTy)->getElementType(),
1725  *DstEltTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(DstTy)->getElementType();
1726 
1727  if (DstEltType->isBooleanType()) {
1728  assert((SrcEltTy->isFloatingPointTy() ||
1729  isa<llvm::IntegerType>(SrcEltTy)) && "Unknown boolean conversion");
1730 
1731  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(SrcTy);
1732  if (SrcEltTy->isFloatingPointTy()) {
1733  return Builder.CreateFCmpUNE(Src, Zero, "tobool");
1734  } else {
1735  return Builder.CreateICmpNE(Src, Zero, "tobool");
1736  }
1737  }
1738 
1739  // We have the arithmetic types: real int/float.
1740  Value *Res = nullptr;
1741 
1742  if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(SrcEltTy)) {
1743  bool InputSigned = SrcEltType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
1744  if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(DstEltTy))
1745  Res = Builder.CreateIntCast(Src, DstTy, InputSigned, "conv");
1746  else if (InputSigned)
1747  Res = Builder.CreateSIToFP(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1748  else
1749  Res = Builder.CreateUIToFP(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1750  } else if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(DstEltTy)) {
1751  assert(SrcEltTy->isFloatingPointTy() && "Unknown real conversion");
1752  if (DstEltType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType())
1753  Res = Builder.CreateFPToSI(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1754  else
1755  Res = Builder.CreateFPToUI(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1756  } else {
1757  assert(SrcEltTy->isFloatingPointTy() && DstEltTy->isFloatingPointTy() &&
1758  "Unknown real conversion");
1759  if (DstEltTy->getTypeID() < SrcEltTy->getTypeID())
1760  Res = Builder.CreateFPTrunc(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1761  else
1762  Res = Builder.CreateFPExt(Src, DstTy, "conv");
1763  }
1764 
1765  return Res;
1766 }
1767 
1768 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitMemberExpr(MemberExpr *E) {
1769  if (CodeGenFunction::ConstantEmission Constant = CGF.tryEmitAsConstant(E)) {
1770  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getBase());
1771  return CGF.emitScalarConstant(Constant, E);
1772  } else {
1773  Expr::EvalResult Result;
1774  if (E->EvaluateAsInt(Result, CGF.getContext(), Expr::SE_AllowSideEffects)) {
1775  llvm::APSInt Value = Result.Val.getInt();
1776  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getBase());
1777  return Builder.getInt(Value);
1778  }
1779  }
1780 
1781  return EmitLoadOfLValue(E);
1782 }
1783 
1784 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitArraySubscriptExpr(ArraySubscriptExpr *E) {
1785  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
1786 
1787  // Emit subscript expressions in rvalue context's. For most cases, this just
1788  // loads the lvalue formed by the subscript expr. However, we have to be
1789  // careful, because the base of a vector subscript is occasionally an rvalue,
1790  // so we can't get it as an lvalue.
1791  if (!E->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType())
1792  return EmitLoadOfLValue(E);
1793 
1794  // Handle the vector case. The base must be a vector, the index must be an
1795  // integer value.
1796  Value *Base = Visit(E->getBase());
1797  Value *Idx = Visit(E->getIdx());
1798  QualType IdxTy = E->getIdx()->getType();
1799 
1800  if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds))
1801  CGF.EmitBoundsCheck(E, E->getBase(), Idx, IdxTy, /*Accessed*/true);
1802 
1803  return Builder.CreateExtractElement(Base, Idx, "vecext");
1804 }
1805 
1806 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitMatrixSubscriptExpr(MatrixSubscriptExpr *E) {
1807  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
1808 
1809  // Handle the vector case. The base must be a vector, the index must be an
1810  // integer value.
1811  Value *RowIdx = Visit(E->getRowIdx());
1812  Value *ColumnIdx = Visit(E->getColumnIdx());
1813 
1814  const auto *MatrixTy = E->getBase()->getType()->castAs<ConstantMatrixType>();
1815  unsigned NumRows = MatrixTy->getNumRows();
1816  llvm::MatrixBuilder MB(Builder);
1817  Value *Idx = MB.CreateIndex(RowIdx, ColumnIdx, NumRows);
1818  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0)
1819  MB.CreateIndexAssumption(Idx, MatrixTy->getNumElementsFlattened());
1820 
1821  Value *Matrix = Visit(E->getBase());
1822 
1823  // TODO: Should we emit bounds checks with SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds?
1824  return Builder.CreateExtractElement(Matrix, Idx, "matrixext");
1825 }
1826 
1827 static int getMaskElt(llvm::ShuffleVectorInst *SVI, unsigned Idx,
1828  unsigned Off) {
1829  int MV = SVI->getMaskValue(Idx);
1830  if (MV == -1)
1831  return -1;
1832  return Off + MV;
1833 }
1834 
1835 static int getAsInt32(llvm::ConstantInt *C, llvm::Type *I32Ty) {
1836  assert(llvm::ConstantInt::isValueValidForType(I32Ty, C->getZExtValue()) &&
1837  "Index operand too large for shufflevector mask!");
1838  return C->getZExtValue();
1839 }
1840 
1841 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitInitListExpr(InitListExpr *E) {
1842  bool Ignore = TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
1843  (void)Ignore;
1844  assert (Ignore == false && "init list ignored");
1845  unsigned NumInitElements = E->getNumInits();
1846 
1847  if (E->hadArrayRangeDesignator())
1848  CGF.ErrorUnsupported(E, "GNU array range designator extension");
1849 
1850  llvm::VectorType *VType =
1851  dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(ConvertType(E->getType()));
1852 
1853  if (!VType) {
1854  if (NumInitElements == 0) {
1855  // C++11 value-initialization for the scalar.
1856  return EmitNullValue(E->getType());
1857  }
1858  // We have a scalar in braces. Just use the first element.
1859  return Visit(E->getInit(0));
1860  }
1861 
1862  unsigned ResElts = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(VType)->getNumElements();
1863 
1864  // Loop over initializers collecting the Value for each, and remembering
1865  // whether the source was swizzle (ExtVectorElementExpr). This will allow
1866  // us to fold the shuffle for the swizzle into the shuffle for the vector
1867  // initializer, since LLVM optimizers generally do not want to touch
1868  // shuffles.
1869  unsigned CurIdx = 0;
1870  bool VIsUndefShuffle = false;
1871  llvm::Value *V = llvm::UndefValue::get(VType);
1872  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumInitElements; ++i) {
1873  Expr *IE = E->getInit(i);
1874  Value *Init = Visit(IE);
1875  SmallVector<int, 16> Args;
1876 
1877  llvm::VectorType *VVT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(Init->getType());
1878 
1879  // Handle scalar elements. If the scalar initializer is actually one
1880  // element of a different vector of the same width, use shuffle instead of
1881  // extract+insert.
1882  if (!VVT) {
1883  if (isa<ExtVectorElementExpr>(IE)) {
1884  llvm::ExtractElementInst *EI = cast<llvm::ExtractElementInst>(Init);
1885 
1886  if (cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(EI->getVectorOperandType())
1887  ->getNumElements() == ResElts) {
1888  llvm::ConstantInt *C = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(EI->getIndexOperand());
1889  Value *LHS = nullptr, *RHS = nullptr;
1890  if (CurIdx == 0) {
1891  // insert into undef -> shuffle (src, undef)
1892  // shufflemask must use an i32
1893  Args.push_back(getAsInt32(C, CGF.Int32Ty));
1894  Args.resize(ResElts, -1);
1895 
1896  LHS = EI->getVectorOperand();
1897  RHS = V;
1898  VIsUndefShuffle = true;
1899  } else if (VIsUndefShuffle) {
1900  // insert into undefshuffle && size match -> shuffle (v, src)
1901  llvm::ShuffleVectorInst *SVV = cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(V);
1902  for (unsigned j = 0; j != CurIdx; ++j)
1903  Args.push_back(getMaskElt(SVV, j, 0));
1904  Args.push_back(ResElts + C->getZExtValue());
1905  Args.resize(ResElts, -1);
1906 
1907  LHS = cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(V)->getOperand(0);
1908  RHS = EI->getVectorOperand();
1909  VIsUndefShuffle = false;
1910  }
1911  if (!Args.empty()) {
1912  V = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(LHS, RHS, Args);
1913  ++CurIdx;
1914  continue;
1915  }
1916  }
1917  }
1918  V = Builder.CreateInsertElement(V, Init, Builder.getInt32(CurIdx),
1919  "vecinit");
1920  VIsUndefShuffle = false;
1921  ++CurIdx;
1922  continue;
1923  }
1924 
1925  unsigned InitElts = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(VVT)->getNumElements();
1926 
1927  // If the initializer is an ExtVecEltExpr (a swizzle), and the swizzle's
1928  // input is the same width as the vector being constructed, generate an
1929  // optimized shuffle of the swizzle input into the result.
1930  unsigned Offset = (CurIdx == 0) ? 0 : ResElts;
1931  if (isa<ExtVectorElementExpr>(IE)) {
1932  llvm::ShuffleVectorInst *SVI = cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(Init);
1933  Value *SVOp = SVI->getOperand(0);
1934  auto *OpTy = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(SVOp->getType());
1935 
1936  if (OpTy->getNumElements() == ResElts) {
1937  for (unsigned j = 0; j != CurIdx; ++j) {
1938  // If the current vector initializer is a shuffle with undef, merge
1939  // this shuffle directly into it.
1940  if (VIsUndefShuffle) {
1941  Args.push_back(getMaskElt(cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(V), j, 0));
1942  } else {
1943  Args.push_back(j);
1944  }
1945  }
1946  for (unsigned j = 0, je = InitElts; j != je; ++j)
1947  Args.push_back(getMaskElt(SVI, j, Offset));
1948  Args.resize(ResElts, -1);
1949 
1950  if (VIsUndefShuffle)
1951  V = cast<llvm::ShuffleVectorInst>(V)->getOperand(0);
1952 
1953  Init = SVOp;
1954  }
1955  }
1956 
1957  // Extend init to result vector length, and then shuffle its contribution
1958  // to the vector initializer into V.
1959  if (Args.empty()) {
1960  for (unsigned j = 0; j != InitElts; ++j)
1961  Args.push_back(j);
1962  Args.resize(ResElts, -1);
1963  Init = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Init, Args, "vext");
1964 
1965  Args.clear();
1966  for (unsigned j = 0; j != CurIdx; ++j)
1967  Args.push_back(j);
1968  for (unsigned j = 0; j != InitElts; ++j)
1969  Args.push_back(j + Offset);
1970  Args.resize(ResElts, -1);
1971  }
1972 
1973  // If V is undef, make sure it ends up on the RHS of the shuffle to aid
1974  // merging subsequent shuffles into this one.
1975  if (CurIdx == 0)
1976  std::swap(V, Init);
1977  V = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(V, Init, Args, "vecinit");
1978  VIsUndefShuffle = isa<llvm::UndefValue>(Init);
1979  CurIdx += InitElts;
1980  }
1981 
1982  // FIXME: evaluate codegen vs. shuffling against constant null vector.
1983  // Emit remaining default initializers.
1984  llvm::Type *EltTy = VType->getElementType();
1985 
1986  // Emit remaining default initializers
1987  for (/* Do not initialize i*/; CurIdx < ResElts; ++CurIdx) {
1988  Value *Idx = Builder.getInt32(CurIdx);
1989  llvm::Value *Init = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(EltTy);
1990  V = Builder.CreateInsertElement(V, Init, Idx, "vecinit");
1991  }
1992  return V;
1993 }
1994 
1995 bool CodeGenFunction::ShouldNullCheckClassCastValue(const CastExpr *CE) {
1996  const Expr *E = CE->getSubExpr();
1997 
1998  if (CE->getCastKind() == CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase)
1999  return false;
2000 
2001  if (isa<CXXThisExpr>(E->IgnoreParens())) {
2002  // We always assume that 'this' is never null.
2003  return false;
2004  }
2005 
2006  if (const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(CE)) {
2007  // And that glvalue casts are never null.
2008  if (ICE->isGLValue())
2009  return false;
2010  }
2011 
2012  return true;
2013 }
2014 
2015 // VisitCastExpr - Emit code for an explicit or implicit cast. Implicit casts
2016 // have to handle a more broad range of conversions than explicit casts, as they
2017 // handle things like function to ptr-to-function decay etc.
2018 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitCastExpr(CastExpr *CE) {
2019  Expr *E = CE->getSubExpr();
2020  QualType DestTy = CE->getType();
2021  CastKind Kind = CE->getCastKind();
2022 
2023  // These cases are generally not written to ignore the result of
2024  // evaluating their sub-expressions, so we clear this now.
2025  bool Ignored = TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
2026 
2027  // Since almost all cast kinds apply to scalars, this switch doesn't have
2028  // a default case, so the compiler will warn on a missing case. The cases
2029  // are in the same order as in the CastKind enum.
2030  switch (Kind) {
2031  case CK_Dependent: llvm_unreachable("dependent cast kind in IR gen!");
2032  case CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr:
2033  llvm_unreachable("builtin functions are handled elsewhere");
2034 
2035  case CK_LValueBitCast:
2036  case CK_ObjCObjectLValueCast: {
2037  Address Addr = EmitLValue(E).getAddress(CGF);
2038  Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(DestTy));
2039  LValue LV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, DestTy);
2040  return EmitLoadOfLValue(LV, CE->getExprLoc());
2041  }
2042 
2043  case CK_LValueToRValueBitCast: {
2044  LValue SourceLVal = CGF.EmitLValue(E);
2045  Address Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(SourceLVal.getAddress(CGF),
2046  CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(DestTy));
2047  LValue DestLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, DestTy);
2048  DestLV.setTBAAInfo(TBAAAccessInfo::getMayAliasInfo());
2049  return EmitLoadOfLValue(DestLV, CE->getExprLoc());
2050  }
2051 
2052  case CK_CPointerToObjCPointerCast:
2053  case CK_BlockPointerToObjCPointerCast:
2054  case CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast:
2055  case CK_BitCast: {
2056  Value *Src = Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2057  llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
2058  llvm::Type *DstTy = ConvertType(DestTy);
2059  if (SrcTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() && DstTy->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() &&
2060  SrcTy->getPointerAddressSpace() != DstTy->getPointerAddressSpace()) {
2061  llvm_unreachable("wrong cast for pointers in different address spaces"
2062  "(must be an address space cast)!");
2063  }
2064 
2065  if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast)) {
2066  if (auto *PT = DestTy->getAs<PointerType>()) {
2067  CGF.EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(
2068  PT->getPointeeType(),
2069  Address(Src,
2070  CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(
2071  E->getType()->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()),
2072  CGF.getPointerAlign()),
2073  /*MayBeNull=*/true, CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_UnrelatedCast,
2074  CE->getBeginLoc());
2075  }
2076  }
2077 
2078  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers) {
2079  const QualType SrcType = E->getType();
2080 
2081  if (SrcType.mayBeNotDynamicClass() && DestTy.mayBeDynamicClass()) {
2082  // Casting to pointer that could carry dynamic information (provided by
2083  // invariant.group) requires launder.
2084  Src = Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(Src);
2085  } else if (SrcType.mayBeDynamicClass() && DestTy.mayBeNotDynamicClass()) {
2086  // Casting to pointer that does not carry dynamic information (provided
2087  // by invariant.group) requires stripping it. Note that we don't do it
2088  // if the source could not be dynamic type and destination could be
2089  // dynamic because dynamic information is already laundered. It is
2090  // because launder(strip(src)) == launder(src), so there is no need to
2091  // add extra strip before launder.
2092  Src = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(Src);
2093  }
2094  }
2095 
2096  // Update heapallocsite metadata when there is an explicit pointer cast.
2097  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<llvm::CallBase>(Src)) {
2098  if (CI->getMetadata("heapallocsite") && isa<ExplicitCastExpr>(CE)) {
2099  QualType PointeeType = DestTy->getPointeeType();
2100  if (!PointeeType.isNull())
2101  CGF.getDebugInfo()->addHeapAllocSiteMetadata(CI, PointeeType,
2102  CE->getExprLoc());
2103  }
2104  }
2105 
2106  // If Src is a fixed vector and Dst is a scalable vector, and both have the
2107  // same element type, use the llvm.experimental.vector.insert intrinsic to
2108  // perform the bitcast.
2109  if (const auto *FixedSrc = dyn_cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(SrcTy)) {
2110  if (const auto *ScalableDst = dyn_cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(DstTy)) {
2111  // If we are casting a fixed i8 vector to a scalable 16 x i1 predicate
2112  // vector, use a vector insert and bitcast the result.
2113  bool NeedsBitCast = false;
2114  auto PredType = llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), 16);
2115  llvm::Type *OrigType = DstTy;
2116  if (ScalableDst == PredType &&
2117  FixedSrc->getElementType() == Builder.getInt8Ty()) {
2118  DstTy = llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(Builder.getInt8Ty(), 2);
2119  ScalableDst = cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(DstTy);
2120  NeedsBitCast = true;
2121  }
2122  if (FixedSrc->getElementType() == ScalableDst->getElementType()) {
2123  llvm::Value *UndefVec = llvm::UndefValue::get(DstTy);
2124  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGF.CGM.Int64Ty);
2125  llvm::Value *Result = Builder.CreateInsertVector(
2126  DstTy, UndefVec, Src, Zero, "castScalableSve");
2127  if (NeedsBitCast)
2128  Result = Builder.CreateBitCast(Result, OrigType);
2129  return Result;
2130  }
2131  }
2132  }
2133 
2134  // If Src is a scalable vector and Dst is a fixed vector, and both have the
2135  // same element type, use the llvm.experimental.vector.extract intrinsic to
2136  // perform the bitcast.
2137  if (const auto *ScalableSrc = dyn_cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(SrcTy)) {
2138  if (const auto *FixedDst = dyn_cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(DstTy)) {
2139  // If we are casting a scalable 16 x i1 predicate vector to a fixed i8
2140  // vector, bitcast the source and use a vector extract.
2141  auto PredType = llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(Builder.getInt1Ty(), 16);
2142  if (ScalableSrc == PredType &&
2143  FixedDst->getElementType() == Builder.getInt8Ty()) {
2144  SrcTy = llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(Builder.getInt8Ty(), 2);
2145  ScalableSrc = cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(SrcTy);
2146  Src = Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, SrcTy);
2147  }
2148  if (ScalableSrc->getElementType() == FixedDst->getElementType()) {
2149  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGF.CGM.Int64Ty);
2150  return Builder.CreateExtractVector(DstTy, Src, Zero, "castFixedSve");
2151  }
2152  }
2153  }
2154 
2155  // Perform VLAT <-> VLST bitcast through memory.
2156  // TODO: since the llvm.experimental.vector.{insert,extract} intrinsics
2157  // require the element types of the vectors to be the same, we
2158  // need to keep this around for bitcasts between VLAT <-> VLST where
2159  // the element types of the vectors are not the same, until we figure
2160  // out a better way of doing these casts.
2161  if ((isa<llvm::FixedVectorType>(SrcTy) &&
2162  isa<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(DstTy)) ||
2163  (isa<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(SrcTy) &&
2164  isa<llvm::FixedVectorType>(DstTy))) {
2165  Address Addr = CGF.CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca(SrcTy, "saved-value");
2166  LValue LV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, E->getType());
2167  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Src, LV);
2168  Addr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(DestTy),
2169  "castFixedSve");
2170  LValue DestLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, DestTy);
2171  DestLV.setTBAAInfo(TBAAAccessInfo::getMayAliasInfo());
2172  return EmitLoadOfLValue(DestLV, CE->getExprLoc());
2173  }
2174  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DstTy);
2175  }
2176  case CK_AddressSpaceConversion: {
2177  Expr::EvalResult Result;
2178  if (E->EvaluateAsRValue(Result, CGF.getContext()) &&
2179  Result.Val.isNullPointer()) {
2180  // If E has side effect, it is emitted even if its final result is a
2181  // null pointer. In that case, a DCE pass should be able to
2182  // eliminate the useless instructions emitted during translating E.
2183  if (Result.HasSideEffects)
2184  Visit(E);
2185  return CGF.CGM.getNullPointer(cast<llvm::PointerType>(
2186  ConvertType(DestTy)), DestTy);
2187  }
2188  // Since target may map different address spaces in AST to the same address
2189  // space, an address space conversion may end up as a bitcast.
2190  return CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().performAddrSpaceCast(
2191  CGF, Visit(E), E->getType()->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace(),
2192  DestTy->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace(), ConvertType(DestTy));
2193  }
2194  case CK_AtomicToNonAtomic:
2195  case CK_NonAtomicToAtomic:
2196  case CK_UserDefinedConversion:
2197  return Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2198 
2199  case CK_NoOp: {
2200  llvm::Value *V = Visit(const_cast<Expr *>(E));
2201  if (V) {
2202  // CK_NoOp can model a pointer qualification conversion, which can remove
2203  // an array bound and change the IR type.
2204  // FIXME: Once pointee types are removed from IR, remove this.
2205  llvm::Type *T = ConvertType(DestTy);
2206  if (T != V->getType())
2207  V = Builder.CreateBitCast(V, T);
2208  }
2209  return V;
2210  }
2211 
2212  case CK_BaseToDerived: {
2213  const CXXRecordDecl *DerivedClassDecl = DestTy->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
2214  assert(DerivedClassDecl && "BaseToDerived arg isn't a C++ object pointer!");
2215 
2216  Address Base = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(E);
2217  Address Derived =
2218  CGF.GetAddressOfDerivedClass(Base, DerivedClassDecl,
2219  CE->path_begin(), CE->path_end(),
2220  CGF.ShouldNullCheckClassCastValue(CE));
2221 
2222  // C++11 [expr.static.cast]p11: Behavior is undefined if a downcast is
2223  // performed and the object is not of the derived type.
2224  if (CGF.sanitizePerformTypeCheck())
2225  CGF.EmitTypeCheck(CodeGenFunction::TCK_DowncastPointer, CE->getExprLoc(),
2226  Derived.getPointer(), DestTy->getPointeeType());
2227 
2228  if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast))
2229  CGF.EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(DestTy->getPointeeType(), Derived,
2230  /*MayBeNull=*/true,
2231  CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_DerivedCast,
2232  CE->getBeginLoc());
2233 
2234  return Derived.getPointer();
2235  }
2236  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
2237  case CK_DerivedToBase: {
2238  // The EmitPointerWithAlignment path does this fine; just discard
2239  // the alignment.
2240  return CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(CE).getPointer();
2241  }
2242 
2243  case CK_Dynamic: {
2244  Address V = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(E);
2245  const CXXDynamicCastExpr *DCE = cast<CXXDynamicCastExpr>(CE);
2246  return CGF.EmitDynamicCast(V, DCE);
2247  }
2248 
2249  case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
2250  return CGF.EmitArrayToPointerDecay(E).getPointer();
2251  case CK_FunctionToPointerDecay:
2252  return EmitLValue(E).getPointer(CGF);
2253 
2254  case CK_NullToPointer:
2255  if (MustVisitNullValue(E))
2256  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E);
2257 
2258  return CGF.CGM.getNullPointer(cast<llvm::PointerType>(ConvertType(DestTy)),
2259  DestTy);
2260 
2261  case CK_NullToMemberPointer: {
2262  if (MustVisitNullValue(E))
2263  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E);
2264 
2265  const MemberPointerType *MPT = CE->getType()->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
2266  return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitNullMemberPointer(MPT);
2267  }
2268 
2269  case CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer:
2270  case CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer:
2271  case CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer: {
2272  Value *Src = Visit(E);
2273 
2274  // Note that the AST doesn't distinguish between checked and
2275  // unchecked member pointer conversions, so we always have to
2276  // implement checked conversions here. This is inefficient when
2277  // actual control flow may be required in order to perform the
2278  // check, which it is for data member pointers (but not member
2279  // function pointers on Itanium and ARM).
2280  return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerConversion(CGF, CE, Src);
2281  }
2282 
2283  case CK_ARCProduceObject:
2284  return CGF.EmitARCRetainScalarExpr(E);
2285  case CK_ARCConsumeObject:
2286  return CGF.EmitObjCConsumeObject(E->getType(), Visit(E));
2287  case CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject:
2288  return CGF.EmitARCReclaimReturnedObject(E, /*allowUnsafe*/ Ignored);
2289  case CK_ARCExtendBlockObject:
2290  return CGF.EmitARCExtendBlockObject(E);
2291 
2292  case CK_CopyAndAutoreleaseBlockObject:
2293  return CGF.EmitBlockCopyAndAutorelease(Visit(E), E->getType());
2294 
2295  case CK_FloatingRealToComplex:
2296  case CK_FloatingComplexCast:
2297  case CK_IntegralRealToComplex:
2298  case CK_IntegralComplexCast:
2299  case CK_IntegralComplexToFloatingComplex:
2300  case CK_FloatingComplexToIntegralComplex:
2301  case CK_ConstructorConversion:
2302  case CK_ToUnion:
2303  llvm_unreachable("scalar cast to non-scalar value");
2304 
2305  case CK_LValueToRValue:
2306  assert(CGF.getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType(E->getType(), DestTy));
2307  assert(E->isGLValue() && "lvalue-to-rvalue applied to r-value!");
2308  return Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2309 
2310  case CK_IntegralToPointer: {
2311  Value *Src = Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2312 
2313  // First, convert to the correct width so that we control the kind of
2314  // extension.
2315  auto DestLLVMTy = ConvertType(DestTy);
2316  llvm::Type *MiddleTy = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(DestLLVMTy);
2317  bool InputSigned = E->getType()->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
2318  llvm::Value* IntResult =
2319  Builder.CreateIntCast(Src, MiddleTy, InputSigned, "conv");
2320 
2321  auto *IntToPtr = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(IntResult, DestLLVMTy);
2322 
2323  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers) {
2324  // Going from integer to pointer that could be dynamic requires reloading
2325  // dynamic information from invariant.group.
2326  if (DestTy.mayBeDynamicClass())
2327  IntToPtr = Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(IntToPtr);
2328  }
2329  return IntToPtr;
2330  }
2331  case CK_PointerToIntegral: {
2332  assert(!DestTy->isBooleanType() && "bool should use PointerToBool");
2333  auto *PtrExpr = Visit(E);
2334 
2335  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers) {
2336  const QualType SrcType = E->getType();
2337 
2338  // Casting to integer requires stripping dynamic information as it does
2339  // not carries it.
2340  if (SrcType.mayBeDynamicClass())
2341  PtrExpr = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(PtrExpr);
2342  }
2343 
2344  return Builder.CreatePtrToInt(PtrExpr, ConvertType(DestTy));
2345  }
2346  case CK_ToVoid: {
2347  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E);
2348  return nullptr;
2349  }
2350  case CK_MatrixCast: {
2351  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2352  CE->getExprLoc());
2353  }
2354  case CK_VectorSplat: {
2355  llvm::Type *DstTy = ConvertType(DestTy);
2356  Value *Elt = Visit(const_cast<Expr *>(E));
2357  // Splat the element across to all elements
2358  llvm::ElementCount NumElements =
2359  cast<llvm::VectorType>(DstTy)->getElementCount();
2360  return Builder.CreateVectorSplat(NumElements, Elt, "splat");
2361  }
2362 
2363  case CK_FixedPointCast:
2364  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2365  CE->getExprLoc());
2366 
2367  case CK_FixedPointToBoolean:
2368  assert(E->getType()->isFixedPointType() &&
2369  "Expected src type to be fixed point type");
2370  assert(DestTy->isBooleanType() && "Expected dest type to be boolean type");
2371  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2372  CE->getExprLoc());
2373 
2374  case CK_FixedPointToIntegral:
2375  assert(E->getType()->isFixedPointType() &&
2376  "Expected src type to be fixed point type");
2377  assert(DestTy->isIntegerType() && "Expected dest type to be an integer");
2378  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2379  CE->getExprLoc());
2380 
2381  case CK_IntegralToFixedPoint:
2382  assert(E->getType()->isIntegerType() &&
2383  "Expected src type to be an integer");
2384  assert(DestTy->isFixedPointType() &&
2385  "Expected dest type to be fixed point type");
2386  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2387  CE->getExprLoc());
2388 
2389  case CK_IntegralCast: {
2390  ScalarConversionOpts Opts;
2391  if (auto *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(CE)) {
2392  if (!ICE->isPartOfExplicitCast())
2393  Opts = ScalarConversionOpts(CGF.SanOpts);
2394  }
2395  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2396  CE->getExprLoc(), Opts);
2397  }
2398  case CK_IntegralToFloating:
2399  case CK_FloatingToIntegral:
2400  case CK_FloatingCast:
2401  case CK_FixedPointToFloating:
2402  case CK_FloatingToFixedPoint: {
2403  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, CE);
2404  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2405  CE->getExprLoc());
2406  }
2407  case CK_BooleanToSignedIntegral: {
2408  ScalarConversionOpts Opts;
2409  Opts.TreatBooleanAsSigned = true;
2410  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2411  CE->getExprLoc(), Opts);
2412  }
2413  case CK_IntegralToBoolean:
2414  return EmitIntToBoolConversion(Visit(E));
2415  case CK_PointerToBoolean:
2416  return EmitPointerToBoolConversion(Visit(E), E->getType());
2417  case CK_FloatingToBoolean: {
2418  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, CE);
2419  return EmitFloatToBoolConversion(Visit(E));
2420  }
2421  case CK_MemberPointerToBoolean: {
2422  llvm::Value *MemPtr = Visit(E);
2423  const MemberPointerType *MPT = E->getType()->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
2424  return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(CGF, MemPtr, MPT);
2425  }
2426 
2427  case CK_FloatingComplexToReal:
2428  case CK_IntegralComplexToReal:
2429  return CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E, false, true).first;
2430 
2431  case CK_FloatingComplexToBoolean:
2432  case CK_IntegralComplexToBoolean: {
2433  CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy V = CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E);
2434 
2435  // TODO: kill this function off, inline appropriate case here
2436  return EmitComplexToScalarConversion(V, E->getType(), DestTy,
2437  CE->getExprLoc());
2438  }
2439 
2440  case CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType: {
2441  assert((DestTy->isEventT() || DestTy->isQueueT() ||
2442  DestTy->isOCLIntelSubgroupAVCType()) &&
2443  "CK_ZeroToOCLEvent cast on non-event type");
2444  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(DestTy));
2445  }
2446 
2447  case CK_IntToOCLSampler:
2448  return CGF.CGM.createOpenCLIntToSamplerConversion(E, CGF);
2449 
2450  } // end of switch
2451 
2452  llvm_unreachable("unknown scalar cast");
2453 }
2454 
2455 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitStmtExpr(const StmtExpr *E) {
2456  CodeGenFunction::StmtExprEvaluation eval(CGF);
2457  Address RetAlloca = CGF.EmitCompoundStmt(*E->getSubStmt(),
2458  !E->getType()->isVoidType());
2459  if (!RetAlloca.isValid())
2460  return nullptr;
2461  return CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(CGF.MakeAddrLValue(RetAlloca, E->getType()),
2462  E->getExprLoc());
2463 }
2464 
2465 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitExprWithCleanups(ExprWithCleanups *E) {
2466  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope Scope(CGF);
2467  Value *V = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
2468  // Defend against dominance problems caused by jumps out of expression
2469  // evaluation through the shared cleanup block.
2470  Scope.ForceCleanup({&V});
2471  return V;
2472 }
2473 
2474 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2475 // Unary Operators
2476 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2477 
2478 static BinOpInfo createBinOpInfoFromIncDec(const UnaryOperator *E,
2479  llvm::Value *InVal, bool IsInc,
2480  FPOptions FPFeatures) {
2481  BinOpInfo BinOp;
2482  BinOp.LHS = InVal;
2483  BinOp.RHS = llvm::ConstantInt::get(InVal->getType(), 1, false);
2484  BinOp.Ty = E->getType();
2485  BinOp.Opcode = IsInc ? BO_Add : BO_Sub;
2486  BinOp.FPFeatures = FPFeatures;
2487  BinOp.E = E;
2488  return BinOp;
2489 }
2490 
2491 llvm::Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitIncDecConsiderOverflowBehavior(
2492  const UnaryOperator *E, llvm::Value *InVal, bool IsInc) {
2493  llvm::Value *Amount =
2494  llvm::ConstantInt::get(InVal->getType(), IsInc ? 1 : -1, true);
2495  StringRef Name = IsInc ? "inc" : "dec";
2496  switch (CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior()) {
2497  case LangOptions::SOB_Defined:
2498  return Builder.CreateAdd(InVal, Amount, Name);
2499  case LangOptions::SOB_Undefined:
2500  if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
2501  return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(InVal, Amount, Name);
2502  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2503  case LangOptions::SOB_Trapping:
2504  if (!E->canOverflow())
2505  return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(InVal, Amount, Name);
2506  return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(createBinOpInfoFromIncDec(
2507  E, InVal, IsInc, E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts())));
2508  }
2509  llvm_unreachable("Unknown SignedOverflowBehaviorTy");
2510 }
2511 
2512 namespace {
2513 /// Handles check and update for lastprivate conditional variables.
2514 class OMPLastprivateConditionalUpdateRAII {
2515 private:
2516  CodeGenFunction &CGF;
2517  const UnaryOperator *E;
2518 
2519 public:
2520  OMPLastprivateConditionalUpdateRAII(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2521  const UnaryOperator *E)
2522  : CGF(CGF), E(E) {}
2523  ~OMPLastprivateConditionalUpdateRAII() {
2524  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMP)
2525  CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().checkAndEmitLastprivateConditional(
2526  CGF, E->getSubExpr());
2527  }
2528 };
2529 } // namespace
2530 
2531 llvm::Value *
2532 ScalarExprEmitter::EmitScalarPrePostIncDec(const UnaryOperator *E, LValue LV,
2533  bool isInc, bool isPre) {
2534  OMPLastprivateConditionalUpdateRAII OMPRegion(CGF, E);
2535  QualType type = E->getSubExpr()->getType();
2536  llvm::PHINode *atomicPHI = nullptr;
2537  llvm::Value *value;
2538  llvm::Value *input;
2539 
2540  int amount = (isInc ? 1 : -1);
2541  bool isSubtraction = !isInc;
2542 
2543  if (const AtomicType *atomicTy = type->getAs<AtomicType>()) {
2544  type = atomicTy->getValueType();
2545  if (isInc && type->isBooleanType()) {
2546  llvm::Value *True = CGF.EmitToMemory(Builder.getTrue(), type);
2547  if (isPre) {
2548  Builder.CreateStore(True, LV.getAddress(CGF), LV.isVolatileQualified())
2549  ->setAtomic(llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
2550  return Builder.getTrue();
2551  }
2552  // For atomic bool increment, we just store true and return it for
2553  // preincrement, do an atomic swap with true for postincrement
2554  return Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(
2555  llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xchg, LV.getPointer(CGF), True,
2556  llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
2557  }
2558  // Special case for atomic increment / decrement on integers, emit
2559  // atomicrmw instructions. We skip this if we want to be doing overflow
2560  // checking, and fall into the slow path with the atomic cmpxchg loop.
2561  if (!type->isBooleanType() && type->isIntegerType() &&
2562  !(type->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
2563  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
2564  CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior() !=
2565  LangOptions::SOB_Trapping) {
2566  llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BinOp aop = isInc ? llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Add :
2567  llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Sub;
2568  llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps op = isInc ? llvm::Instruction::Add :
2569  llvm::Instruction::Sub;
2570  llvm::Value *amt = CGF.EmitToMemory(
2571  llvm::ConstantInt::get(ConvertType(type), 1, true), type);
2572  llvm::Value *old =
2573  Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(aop, LV.getPointer(CGF), amt,
2574  llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
2575  return isPre ? Builder.CreateBinOp(op, old, amt) : old;
2576  }
2577  value = EmitLoadOfLValue(LV, E->getExprLoc());
2578  input = value;
2579  // For every other atomic operation, we need to emit a load-op-cmpxchg loop
2580  llvm::BasicBlock *startBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
2581  llvm::BasicBlock *opBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_op", CGF.CurFn);
2582  value = CGF.EmitToMemory(value, type);
2583  Builder.CreateBr(opBB);
2584  Builder.SetInsertPoint(opBB);
2585  atomicPHI = Builder.CreatePHI(value->getType(), 2);
2586  atomicPHI->addIncoming(value, startBB);
2587  value = atomicPHI;
2588  } else {
2589  value = EmitLoadOfLValue(LV, E->getExprLoc());
2590  input = value;
2591  }
2592 
2593  // Special case of integer increment that we have to check first: bool++.
2594  // Due to promotion rules, we get:
2595  // bool++ -> bool = bool + 1
2596  // -> bool = (int)bool + 1
2597  // -> bool = ((int)bool + 1 != 0)
2598  // An interesting aspect of this is that increment is always true.
2599  // Decrement does not have this property.
2600  if (isInc && type->isBooleanType()) {
2601  value = Builder.getTrue();
2602 
2603  // Most common case by far: integer increment.
2604  } else if (type->isIntegerType()) {
2605  QualType promotedType;
2606  bool canPerformLossyDemotionCheck = false;
2607  if (type->isPromotableIntegerType()) {
2608  promotedType = CGF.getContext().getPromotedIntegerType(type);
2609  assert(promotedType != type && "Shouldn't promote to the same type.");
2610  canPerformLossyDemotionCheck = true;
2611  canPerformLossyDemotionCheck &=
2612  CGF.getContext().getCanonicalType(type) !=
2613  CGF.getContext().getCanonicalType(promotedType);
2614  canPerformLossyDemotionCheck &=
2615  PromotionIsPotentiallyEligibleForImplicitIntegerConversionCheck(
2616  type, promotedType);
2617  assert((!canPerformLossyDemotionCheck ||
2618  type->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType() ||
2619  promotedType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType() ||
2620  ConvertType(type)->getScalarSizeInBits() ==
2621  ConvertType(promotedType)->getScalarSizeInBits()) &&
2622  "The following check expects that if we do promotion to different "
2623  "underlying canonical type, at least one of the types (either "
2624  "base or promoted) will be signed, or the bitwidths will match.");
2625  }
2626  if (CGF.SanOpts.hasOneOf(
2627  SanitizerKind::ImplicitIntegerArithmeticValueChange) &&
2628  canPerformLossyDemotionCheck) {
2629  // While `x += 1` (for `x` with width less than int) is modeled as
2630  // promotion+arithmetics+demotion, and we can catch lossy demotion with
2631  // ease; inc/dec with width less than int can't overflow because of
2632  // promotion rules, so we omit promotion+demotion, which means that we can
2633  // not catch lossy "demotion". Because we still want to catch these cases
2634  // when the sanitizer is enabled, we perform the promotion, then perform
2635  // the increment/decrement in the wider type, and finally
2636  // perform the demotion. This will catch lossy demotions.
2637 
2638  value = EmitScalarConversion(value, type, promotedType, E->getExprLoc());
2639  Value *amt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(value->getType(), amount, true);
2640  value = Builder.CreateAdd(value, amt, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2641  // Do pass non-default ScalarConversionOpts so that sanitizer check is
2642  // emitted.
2643  value = EmitScalarConversion(value, promotedType, type, E->getExprLoc(),
2644  ScalarConversionOpts(CGF.SanOpts));
2645 
2646  // Note that signed integer inc/dec with width less than int can't
2647  // overflow because of promotion rules; we're just eliding a few steps
2648  // here.
2649  } else if (E->canOverflow() && type->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) {
2650  value = EmitIncDecConsiderOverflowBehavior(E, value, isInc);
2651  } else if (E->canOverflow() && type->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
2652  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow)) {
2653  value = EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(createBinOpInfoFromIncDec(
2654  E, value, isInc, E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts())));
2655  } else {
2656  llvm::Value *amt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(value->getType(), amount, true);
2657  value = Builder.CreateAdd(value, amt, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2658  }
2659 
2660  // Next most common: pointer increment.
2661  } else if (const PointerType *ptr = type->getAs<PointerType>()) {
2662  QualType type = ptr->getPointeeType();
2663 
2664  // VLA types don't have constant size.
2665  if (const VariableArrayType *vla
2666  = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(type)) {
2667  llvm::Value *numElts = CGF.getVLASize(vla).NumElts;
2668  if (!isInc) numElts = Builder.CreateNSWNeg(numElts, "vla.negsize");
2669  llvm::Type *elemTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(vla->getElementType());
2670  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
2671  value = Builder.CreateGEP(elemTy, value, numElts, "vla.inc");
2672  else
2673  value = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
2674  elemTy, value, numElts, /*SignedIndices=*/false, isSubtraction,
2675  E->getExprLoc(), "vla.inc");
2676 
2677  // Arithmetic on function pointers (!) is just +-1.
2678  } else if (type->isFunctionType()) {
2679  llvm::Value *amt = Builder.getInt32(amount);
2680 
2681  value = CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(value);
2682  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
2683  value = Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, value, amt, "incdec.funcptr");
2684  else
2685  value = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, value, amt,
2686  /*SignedIndices=*/false,
2687  isSubtraction, E->getExprLoc(),
2688  "incdec.funcptr");
2689  value = Builder.CreateBitCast(value, input->getType());
2690 
2691  // For everything else, we can just do a simple increment.
2692  } else {
2693  llvm::Value *amt = Builder.getInt32(amount);
2694  llvm::Type *elemTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(type);
2695  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
2696  value = Builder.CreateGEP(elemTy, value, amt, "incdec.ptr");
2697  else
2698  value = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
2699  elemTy, value, amt, /*SignedIndices=*/false, isSubtraction,
2700  E->getExprLoc(), "incdec.ptr");
2701  }
2702 
2703  // Vector increment/decrement.
2704  } else if (type->isVectorType()) {
2705  if (type->hasIntegerRepresentation()) {
2706  llvm::Value *amt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(value->getType(), amount);
2707 
2708  value = Builder.CreateAdd(value, amt, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2709  } else {
2710  value = Builder.CreateFAdd(
2711  value,
2712  llvm::ConstantFP::get(value->getType(), amount),
2713  isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2714  }
2715 
2716  // Floating point.
2717  } else if (type->isRealFloatingType()) {
2718  // Add the inc/dec to the real part.
2719  llvm::Value *amt;
2720  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, E);
2721 
2722  if (type->isHalfType() && !CGF.getContext().getLangOpts().NativeHalfType) {
2723  // Another special case: half FP increment should be done via float
2724  if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().useFP16ConversionIntrinsics()) {
2725  value = Builder.CreateCall(
2726  CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::convert_from_fp16,
2727  CGF.CGM.FloatTy),
2728  input, "incdec.conv");
2729  } else {
2730  value = Builder.CreateFPExt(input, CGF.CGM.FloatTy, "incdec.conv");
2731  }
2732  }
2733 
2734  if (value->getType()->isFloatTy())
2735  amt = llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext,
2736  llvm::APFloat(static_cast<float>(amount)));
2737  else if (value->getType()->isDoubleTy())
2738  amt = llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext,
2739  llvm::APFloat(static_cast<double>(amount)));
2740  else {
2741  // Remaining types are Half, LongDouble, __ibm128 or __float128. Convert
2742  // from float.
2743  llvm::APFloat F(static_cast<float>(amount));
2744  bool ignored;
2745  const llvm::fltSemantics *FS;
2746  // Don't use getFloatTypeSemantics because Half isn't
2747  // necessarily represented using the "half" LLVM type.
2748  if (value->getType()->isFP128Ty())
2749  FS = &CGF.getTarget().getFloat128Format();
2750  else if (value->getType()->isHalfTy())
2751  FS = &CGF.getTarget().getHalfFormat();
2752  else if (value->getType()->isPPC_FP128Ty())
2753  FS = &CGF.getTarget().getIbm128Format();
2754  else
2755  FS = &CGF.getTarget().getLongDoubleFormat();
2756  F.convert(*FS, llvm::APFloat::rmTowardZero, &ignored);
2757  amt = llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext, F);
2758  }
2759  value = Builder.CreateFAdd(value, amt, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2760 
2761  if (type->isHalfType() && !CGF.getContext().getLangOpts().NativeHalfType) {
2762  if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().useFP16ConversionIntrinsics()) {
2763  value = Builder.CreateCall(
2764  CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::convert_to_fp16,
2765  CGF.CGM.FloatTy),
2766  value, "incdec.conv");
2767  } else {
2768  value = Builder.CreateFPTrunc(value, input->getType(), "incdec.conv");
2769  }
2770  }
2771 
2772  // Fixed-point types.
2773  } else if (type->isFixedPointType()) {
2774  // Fixed-point types are tricky. In some cases, it isn't possible to
2775  // represent a 1 or a -1 in the type at all. Piggyback off of
2776  // EmitFixedPointBinOp to avoid having to reimplement saturation.
2777  BinOpInfo Info;
2778  Info.E = E;
2779  Info.Ty = E->getType();
2780  Info.Opcode = isInc ? BO_Add : BO_Sub;
2781  Info.LHS = value;
2782  Info.RHS = llvm::ConstantInt::get(value->getType(), 1, false);
2783  // If the type is signed, it's better to represent this as +(-1) or -(-1),
2784  // since -1 is guaranteed to be representable.
2785  if (type->isSignedFixedPointType()) {
2786  Info.Opcode = isInc ? BO_Sub : BO_Add;
2787  Info.RHS = Builder.CreateNeg(Info.RHS);
2788  }
2789  // Now, convert from our invented integer literal to the type of the unary
2790  // op. This will upscale and saturate if necessary. This value can become
2791  // undef in some cases.
2792  llvm::FixedPointBuilder<CGBuilderTy> FPBuilder(Builder);
2793  auto DstSema = CGF.getContext().getFixedPointSemantics(Info.Ty);
2794  Info.RHS = FPBuilder.CreateIntegerToFixed(Info.RHS, true, DstSema);
2795  value = EmitFixedPointBinOp(Info);
2796 
2797  // Objective-C pointer types.
2798  } else {
2799  const ObjCObjectPointerType *OPT = type->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
2800  value = CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(value);
2801 
2802  CharUnits size = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(OPT->getObjectType());
2803  if (!isInc) size = -size;
2804  llvm::Value *sizeValue =
2805  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy, size.getQuantity());
2806 
2807  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
2808  value = Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, value, sizeValue, "incdec.objptr");
2809  else
2810  value = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
2811  CGF.Int8Ty, value, sizeValue, /*SignedIndices=*/false, isSubtraction,
2812  E->getExprLoc(), "incdec.objptr");
2813  value = Builder.CreateBitCast(value, input->getType());
2814  }
2815 
2816  if (atomicPHI) {
2817  llvm::BasicBlock *curBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
2818  llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_cont", CGF.CurFn);
2819  auto Pair = CGF.EmitAtomicCompareExchange(
2820  LV, RValue::get(atomicPHI), RValue::get(value), E->getExprLoc());
2821  llvm::Value *old = CGF.EmitToMemory(Pair.first.getScalarVal(), type);
2822  llvm::Value *success = Pair.second;
2823  atomicPHI->addIncoming(old, curBlock);
2824  Builder.CreateCondBr(success, contBB, atomicPHI->getParent());
2825  Builder.SetInsertPoint(contBB);
2826  return isPre ? value : input;
2827  }
2828 
2829  // Store the updated result through the lvalue.
2830  if (LV.isBitField())
2831  CGF.EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue::get(value), LV, &value);
2832  else
2833  CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(value), LV);
2834 
2835  // If this is a postinc, return the value read from memory, otherwise use the
2836  // updated value.
2837  return isPre ? value : input;
2838 }

2841 
2842 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryMinus(const UnaryOperator *E) {
2843  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
2844  Value *Op = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
2845 
2846  // Generate a unary FNeg for FP ops.
2847  if (Op->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
2848  return Builder.CreateFNeg(Op, "fneg");
2849 
2850  // Emit unary minus with EmitSub so we handle overflow cases etc.
2851  BinOpInfo BinOp;
2852  BinOp.RHS = Op;
2853  BinOp.LHS = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(BinOp.RHS->getType());
2854  BinOp.Ty = E->getType();
2855  BinOp.Opcode = BO_Sub;
2856  BinOp.FPFeatures = E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts());
2857  BinOp.E = E;
2858  return EmitSub(BinOp);
2859 }
2860 
2861 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryNot(const UnaryOperator *E) {
2862  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
2863  Value *Op = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
2864  return Builder.CreateNot(Op, "neg");
2865 }
2866 
2867 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryLNot(const UnaryOperator *E) {
2868  // Perform vector logical not on comparison with zero vector.
2869  if (E->getType()->isVectorType() &&
2870  E->getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getVectorKind() ==
2871  VectorType::GenericVector) {
2872  Value *Oper = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
2873  Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Oper->getType());
2874  Value *Result;
2875  if (Oper->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
2876  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(
2877  CGF, E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts()));
2878  Result = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_OEQ, Oper, Zero, "cmp");
2879  } else
2880  Result = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Oper, Zero, "cmp");
2881  return Builder.CreateSExt(Result, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
2882  }
2883 
2884  // Compare operand to zero.
2885  Value *BoolVal = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getSubExpr());
2886 
2887  // Invert value.
2888  // TODO: Could dynamically modify easy computations here. For example, if
2889  // the operand is an icmp ne, turn into icmp eq.
2890  BoolVal = Builder.CreateNot(BoolVal, "lnot");
2891 
2892  // ZExt result to the expr type.
2893  return Builder.CreateZExt(BoolVal, ConvertType(E->getType()), "lnot.ext");
2894 }
2895 
2896 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitOffsetOfExpr(OffsetOfExpr *E) {
2897  // Try folding the offsetof to a constant.
2898  Expr::EvalResult EVResult;
2899  if (E->EvaluateAsInt(EVResult, CGF.getContext())) {
2900  llvm::APSInt Value = EVResult.Val.getInt();
2901  return Builder.getInt(Value);
2902  }
2903 
2904  // Loop over the components of the offsetof to compute the value.
2905  unsigned n = E->getNumComponents();
2906  llvm::Type* ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
2907  llvm::Value* Result = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ResultType);
2908  QualType CurrentType = E->getTypeSourceInfo()->getType();
2909  for (unsigned i = 0; i != n; ++i) {
2910  OffsetOfNode ON = E->getComponent(i);
2911  llvm::Value *Offset = nullptr;
2912  switch (ON.getKind()) {
2913  case OffsetOfNode::Array: {
2914  // Compute the index
2915  Expr *IdxExpr = E->getIndexExpr(ON.getArrayExprIndex());
2916  llvm::Value* Idx = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(IdxExpr);
2917  bool IdxSigned = IdxExpr->getType()->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
2918  Idx = Builder.CreateIntCast(Idx, ResultType, IdxSigned, "conv");
2919 
2920  // Save the element type
2921  CurrentType =
2922  CGF.getContext().getAsArrayType(CurrentType)->getElementType();
2923 
2924  // Compute the element size
2925  llvm::Value* ElemSize = llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResultType,
2926  CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(CurrentType).getQuantity());
2927 
2928  // Multiply out to compute the result
2929  Offset = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, ElemSize);
2930  break;
2931  }
2932 
2933  case OffsetOfNode::Field: {
2934  FieldDecl *MemberDecl = ON.getField();
2935  RecordDecl *RD = CurrentType->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
2936  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGF.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2937 
2938  // Compute the index of the field in its parent.
2939  unsigned i = 0;
2940  // FIXME: It would be nice if we didn't have to loop here!
2941  for (RecordDecl::field_iterator Field = RD->field_begin(),
2942  FieldEnd = RD->field_end();
2943  Field != FieldEnd; ++Field, ++i) {
2944  if (*Field == MemberDecl)
2945  break;
2946  }
2947  assert(i < RL.getFieldCount() && "offsetof field in wrong type");
2948 
2949  // Compute the offset to the field
2950  int64_t OffsetInt = RL.getFieldOffset(i) /
2951  CGF.getContext().getCharWidth();
2952  Offset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResultType, OffsetInt);
2953 
2954  // Save the element type.
2955  CurrentType = MemberDecl->getType();
2956  break;
2957  }
2958 
2959  case OffsetOfNode::Identifier:
2960  llvm_unreachable("dependent __builtin_offsetof");
2961 
2962  case OffsetOfNode::Base: {
2963  if (ON.getBase()->isVirtual()) {
2964  CGF.ErrorUnsupported(E, "virtual base in offsetof");
2965  continue;
2966  }
2967 
2968  RecordDecl *RD = CurrentType->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
2969  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGF.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2970 
2971  // Save the element type.
2972  CurrentType = ON.getBase()->getType();
2973 
2974  // Compute the offset to the base.
2975  auto *BaseRT = CurrentType->castAs<RecordType>();
2976  auto *BaseRD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(BaseRT->getDecl());
2977  CharUnits OffsetInt = RL.getBaseClassOffset(BaseRD);
2978  Offset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResultType, OffsetInt.getQuantity());
2979  break;
2980  }
2981  }
2982  Result = Builder.CreateAdd(Result, Offset);
2983  }
2984  return Result;
2985 }
2986 
2987 /// VisitUnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr - Return the size or alignment of the type of
2988 /// argument of the sizeof expression as an integer.
2989 Value *
2990 ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr(
2991  const UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *E) {
2992  QualType TypeToSize = E->getTypeOfArgument();
2993  if (E->getKind() == UETT_SizeOf) {
2994  if (const VariableArrayType *VAT =
2995  CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(TypeToSize)) {
2996  if (E->isArgumentType()) {
2997  // sizeof(type) - make sure to emit the VLA size.
2998  CGF.EmitVariablyModifiedType(TypeToSize);
2999  } else {
3000  // C99 6.5.3.4p2: If the argument is an expression of type
3001  // VLA, it is evaluated.
3002  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getArgumentExpr());
3003  }
3004 
3005  auto VlaSize = CGF.getVLASize(VAT);
3006  llvm::Value *size = VlaSize.NumElts;
3007 
3008  // Scale the number of non-VLA elements by the non-VLA element size.
3009  CharUnits eltSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(VlaSize.Type);
3010  if (!eltSize.isOne())
3011  size = CGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(CGF.CGM.getSize(eltSize), size);
3012 
3013  return size;
3014  }
3015  } else if (E->getKind() == UETT_OpenMPRequiredSimdAlign) {
3016  auto Alignment =
3017  CGF.getContext()
3018  .toCharUnitsFromBits(CGF.getContext().getOpenMPDefaultSimdAlign(
3019  E->getTypeOfArgument()->getPointeeType()))
3020  .getQuantity();
3021  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy, Alignment);
3022  }
3023 
3024  // If this isn't sizeof(vla), the result must be constant; use the constant
3025  // folding logic so we don't have to duplicate it here.
3026  return Builder.getInt(E->EvaluateKnownConstInt(CGF.getContext()));
3027 }
3028 
3029 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryReal(const UnaryOperator *E) {
3030  Expr *Op = E->getSubExpr();
3031  if (Op->getType()->isAnyComplexType()) {
3032  // If it's an l-value, load through the appropriate subobject l-value.
3033  // Note that we have to ask E because Op might be an l-value that
3034  // this won't work for, e.g. an Obj-C property.
3035  if (E->isGLValue())
3036  return CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(CGF.EmitLValue(E),
3037  E->getExprLoc()).getScalarVal();
3038 
3039  // Otherwise, calculate and project.
3040  return CGF.EmitComplexExpr(Op, false, true).first;
3041  }
3042 
3043  return Visit(Op);
3044 }
3045 
3046 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryImag(const UnaryOperator *E) {
3047  Expr *Op = E->getSubExpr();
3048  if (Op->getType()->isAnyComplexType()) {
3049  // If it's an l-value, load through the appropriate subobject l-value.
3050  // Note that we have to ask E because Op might be an l-value that
3051  // this won't work for, e.g. an Obj-C property.
3052  if (Op->isGLValue())
3053  return CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(CGF.EmitLValue(E),
3054  E->getExprLoc()).getScalarVal();
3055 
3056  // Otherwise, calculate and project.
3057  return CGF.EmitComplexExpr(Op, true, false).second;
3058  }
3059 
3060  // __imag on a scalar returns zero. Emit the subexpr to ensure side
3061  // effects are evaluated, but not the actual value.
3062  if (Op->isGLValue())
3063  CGF.EmitLValue(Op);
3064  else
3065  CGF.EmitScalarExpr(Op, true);
3066  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(E->getType()));
3067 }
