3069 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3070 // Binary Operators
3071 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3072 
3073 BinOpInfo ScalarExprEmitter::EmitBinOps(const BinaryOperator *E) {
3074  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
3075  BinOpInfo Result;
3076  Result.LHS = Visit(E->getLHS());
3077  Result.RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
3078  Result.Ty = E->getType();
3079  Result.Opcode = E->getOpcode();
3080  Result.FPFeatures = E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts());
3081  Result.E = E;
3082  return Result;
3083 }
3084 
3085 LValue ScalarExprEmitter::EmitCompoundAssignLValue(
3086  const CompoundAssignOperator *E,
3087  Value *(ScalarExprEmitter::*Func)(const BinOpInfo &),
3088  Value *&Result) {
3089  QualType LHSTy = E->getLHS()->getType();
3090  BinOpInfo OpInfo;
3091 
3092  if (E->getComputationResultType()->isAnyComplexType())
3093  return CGF.EmitScalarCompoundAssignWithComplex(E, Result);
3094 
3095  // Emit the RHS first. __block variables need to have the rhs evaluated
3096  // first, plus this should improve codegen a little.
3097  OpInfo.RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
3098  OpInfo.Ty = E->getComputationResultType();
3099  OpInfo.Opcode = E->getOpcode();
3100  OpInfo.FPFeatures = E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts());
3101  OpInfo.E = E;
3102  // Load/convert the LHS.
3103  LValue LHSLV = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), CodeGenFunction::TCK_Store);
3104 
3105  llvm::PHINode *atomicPHI = nullptr;
3106  if (const AtomicType *atomicTy = LHSTy->getAs<AtomicType>()) {
3107  QualType type = atomicTy->getValueType();
3108  if (!type->isBooleanType() && type->isIntegerType() &&
3109  !(type->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
3110  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
3111  CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior() !=
3112  LangOptions::SOB_Trapping) {
3113  llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BinOp AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BAD_BINOP;
3114  llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps Op;
3115  switch (OpInfo.Opcode) {
3116  // We don't have atomicrmw operands for *, %, /, <<, >>
3117  case BO_MulAssign: case BO_DivAssign:
3118  case BO_RemAssign:
3119  case BO_ShlAssign:
3120  case BO_ShrAssign:
3121  break;
3122  case BO_AddAssign:
3123  AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Add;
3124  Op = llvm::Instruction::Add;
3125  break;
3126  case BO_SubAssign:
3127  AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Sub;
3128  Op = llvm::Instruction::Sub;
3129  break;
3130  case BO_AndAssign:
3131  AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::And;
3132  Op = llvm::Instruction::And;
3133  break;
3134  case BO_XorAssign:
3135  AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xor;
3136  Op = llvm::Instruction::Xor;
3137  break;
3138  case BO_OrAssign:
3139  AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Or;
3140  Op = llvm::Instruction::Or;
3141  break;
3142  default:
3143  llvm_unreachable("Invalid compound assignment type");
3144  }
3145  if (AtomicOp != llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BAD_BINOP) {
3146  llvm::Value *Amt = CGF.EmitToMemory(
3147  EmitScalarConversion(OpInfo.RHS, E->getRHS()->getType(), LHSTy,
3148  E->getExprLoc()),
3149  LHSTy);
3150  Value *OldVal = Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(
3151  AtomicOp, LHSLV.getPointer(CGF), Amt,
3152  llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
3153 
3154  // Since operation is atomic, the result type is guaranteed to be the
3155  // same as the input in LLVM terms.
3156  Result = Builder.CreateBinOp(Op, OldVal, Amt);
3157  return LHSLV;
3158  }
3159  }
3160  // FIXME: For floating point types, we should be saving and restoring the
3161  // floating point environment in the loop.
3162  llvm::BasicBlock *startBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3163  llvm::BasicBlock *opBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_op", CGF.CurFn);
3164  OpInfo.LHS = EmitLoadOfLValue(LHSLV, E->getExprLoc());
3165  OpInfo.LHS = CGF.EmitToMemory(OpInfo.LHS, type);
3166  Builder.CreateBr(opBB);
3167  Builder.SetInsertPoint(opBB);
3168  atomicPHI = Builder.CreatePHI(OpInfo.LHS->getType(), 2);
3169  atomicPHI->addIncoming(OpInfo.LHS, startBB);
3170  OpInfo.LHS = atomicPHI;
3171  }
3172  else
3173  OpInfo.LHS = EmitLoadOfLValue(LHSLV, E->getExprLoc());
3174 
3175  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, OpInfo.FPFeatures);
3176  SourceLocation Loc = E->getExprLoc();
3177  OpInfo.LHS =
3178  EmitScalarConversion(OpInfo.LHS, LHSTy, E->getComputationLHSType(), Loc);
3179 
3180  // Expand the binary operator.
3181  Result = (this->*Func)(OpInfo);
3182 
3183  // Convert the result back to the LHS type,
3184  // potentially with Implicit Conversion sanitizer check.
3185  Result = EmitScalarConversion(Result, E->getComputationResultType(), LHSTy,
3186  Loc, ScalarConversionOpts(CGF.SanOpts));
3187 
3188  if (atomicPHI) {
3189  llvm::BasicBlock *curBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3190  llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_cont", CGF.CurFn);
3191  auto Pair = CGF.EmitAtomicCompareExchange(
3192  LHSLV, RValue::get(atomicPHI), RValue::get(Result), E->getExprLoc());
3193  llvm::Value *old = CGF.EmitToMemory(Pair.first.getScalarVal(), LHSTy);
3194  llvm::Value *success = Pair.second;
3195  atomicPHI->addIncoming(old, curBlock);
3196  Builder.CreateCondBr(success, contBB, atomicPHI->getParent());
3197  Builder.SetInsertPoint(contBB);
3198  return LHSLV;
3199  }
3200 
3201  // Store the result value into the LHS lvalue. Bit-fields are handled
3202  // specially because the result is altered by the store, i.e., [C99 6.5.16p1]
3203  // 'An assignment expression has the value of the left operand after the
3204  // assignment...'.
3205  if (LHSLV.isBitField())
3206  CGF.EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue::get(Result), LHSLV, &Result);
3207  else
3208  CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(Result), LHSLV);
3209 
3210  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMP)
3211  CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().checkAndEmitLastprivateConditional(CGF,
3212  E->getLHS());
3213  return LHSLV;
3214 }
3215 
3216 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitCompoundAssign(const CompoundAssignOperator *E,
3217  Value *(ScalarExprEmitter::*Func)(const BinOpInfo &)) {
3218  bool Ignore = TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
3219  Value *RHS = nullptr;
3220  LValue LHS = EmitCompoundAssignLValue(E, Func, RHS);
3221 
3222  // If the result is clearly ignored, return now.
3223  if (Ignore)
3224  return nullptr;
3225 
3226  // The result of an assignment in C is the assigned r-value.
3227  if (!CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
3228  return RHS;
3229 
3230  // If the lvalue is non-volatile, return the computed value of the assignment.
3231  if (!LHS.isVolatileQualified())
3232  return RHS;
3233 
3234  // Otherwise, reload the value.
3235  return EmitLoadOfLValue(LHS, E->getExprLoc());
3236 }
3237 
3238 void ScalarExprEmitter::EmitUndefinedBehaviorIntegerDivAndRemCheck(
3239  const BinOpInfo &Ops, llvm::Value *Zero, bool isDiv) {
3240  SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 2> Checks;
3241 
3242  if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero)) {
3243  Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(Builder.CreateICmpNE(Ops.RHS, Zero),
3244  SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero));
3245  }
3246 
3247  const auto *BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(Ops.E);
3248  if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow) &&
3249  Ops.Ty->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation() &&
3250  !IsWidenedIntegerOp(CGF.getContext(), BO->getLHS()) &&
3251  Ops.mayHaveIntegerOverflow()) {
3252  llvm::IntegerType *Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Zero->getType());
3253 
3254  llvm::Value *IntMin =
3255  Builder.getInt(llvm::APInt::getSignedMinValue(Ty->getBitWidth()));
3256  llvm::Value *NegOne = llvm::Constant::getAllOnesValue(Ty);
3257 
3258  llvm::Value *LHSCmp = Builder.CreateICmpNE(Ops.LHS, IntMin);
3259  llvm::Value *RHSCmp = Builder.CreateICmpNE(Ops.RHS, NegOne);
3260  llvm::Value *NotOverflow = Builder.CreateOr(LHSCmp, RHSCmp, "or");
3261  Checks.push_back(
3262  std::make_pair(NotOverflow, SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow));
3263  }
3264 
3265  if (Checks.size() > 0)
3266  EmitBinOpCheck(Checks, Ops);
3267 }
3268 
3269 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitDiv(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
3270  {
3271  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
3272  if ((CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero) ||
3273  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
3274  Ops.Ty->isIntegerType() &&
3275  (Ops.mayHaveIntegerDivisionByZero() || Ops.mayHaveIntegerOverflow())) {
3276  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(Ops.Ty));
3277  EmitUndefinedBehaviorIntegerDivAndRemCheck(Ops, Zero, true);
3278  } else if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::FloatDivideByZero) &&
3279  Ops.Ty->isRealFloatingType() &&
3280  Ops.mayHaveFloatDivisionByZero()) {
3281  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(Ops.Ty));
3282  llvm::Value *NonZero = Builder.CreateFCmpUNE(Ops.RHS, Zero);
3283  EmitBinOpCheck(std::make_pair(NonZero, SanitizerKind::FloatDivideByZero),
3284  Ops);
3285  }
3286  }
3287 
3288  if (Ops.Ty->isConstantMatrixType()) {
3289  llvm::MatrixBuilder MB(Builder);
3290  // We need to check the types of the operands of the operator to get the
3291  // correct matrix dimensions.
3292  auto *BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(Ops.E);
3293  (void)BO;
3294  assert(
3295  isa<ConstantMatrixType>(BO->getLHS()->getType().getCanonicalType()) &&
3296  "first operand must be a matrix");
3297  assert(BO->getRHS()->getType().getCanonicalType()->isArithmeticType() &&
3298  "second operand must be an arithmetic type");
3299  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, Ops.FPFeatures);
3300  return MB.CreateScalarDiv(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS,
3301  Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation());
3302  }
3303 
3304  if (Ops.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
3305  llvm::Value *Val;
3306  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, Ops.FPFeatures);
3307  Val = Builder.CreateFDiv(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "div");
3308  if ((CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
3309  !CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OpenCLCorrectlyRoundedDivSqrt) ||
3310  (CGF.getLangOpts().HIP && CGF.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice &&
3311  !CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().HIPCorrectlyRoundedDivSqrt)) {
3312  // OpenCL v1.1 s7.4: minimum accuracy of single precision / is 2.5ulp
3313  // OpenCL v1.2 s5.6.4.2: The -cl-fp32-correctly-rounded-divide-sqrt
3314  // build option allows an application to specify that single precision
3315  // floating-point divide (x/y and 1/x) and sqrt used in the program
3316  // source are correctly rounded.
3317  llvm::Type *ValTy = Val->getType();
3318  if (ValTy->isFloatTy() ||
3319  (isa<llvm::VectorType>(ValTy) &&
3320  cast<llvm::VectorType>(ValTy)->getElementType()->isFloatTy()))
3321  CGF.SetFPAccuracy(Val, 2.5);
3322  }
3323  return Val;
3324  }
3325  else if (Ops.isFixedPointOp())
3326  return EmitFixedPointBinOp(Ops);
3327  else if (Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation())
3328  return Builder.CreateUDiv(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "div");
3329  else
3330  return Builder.CreateSDiv(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "div");
3331 }
3332 
3333 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitRem(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
3334  // Rem in C can't be a floating point type: C99 6.5.5p2.
3335  if ((CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero) ||
3336  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
3337  Ops.Ty->isIntegerType() &&
3338  (Ops.mayHaveIntegerDivisionByZero() || Ops.mayHaveIntegerOverflow())) {
3339  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
3340  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(Ops.Ty));
3341  EmitUndefinedBehaviorIntegerDivAndRemCheck(Ops, Zero, false);
3342  }
3343 
3344  if (Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation())
3345  return Builder.CreateURem(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "rem");
3346  else
3347  return Builder.CreateSRem(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "rem");
3348 }
3349 
3350 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
3351  unsigned IID;
3352  unsigned OpID = 0;
3353  SanitizerHandler OverflowKind;
3354 
3355  bool isSigned = Ops.Ty->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
3356  switch (Ops.Opcode) {
3357  case BO_Add:
3358  case BO_AddAssign:
3359  OpID = 1;
3360  IID = isSigned ? llvm::Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow :
3361  llvm::Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow;
3362  OverflowKind = SanitizerHandler::AddOverflow;
3363  break;
3364  case BO_Sub:
3365  case BO_SubAssign:
3366  OpID = 2;
3367  IID = isSigned ? llvm::Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow :
3368  llvm::Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow;
3369  OverflowKind = SanitizerHandler::SubOverflow;
3370  break;
3371  case BO_Mul:
3372  case BO_MulAssign:
3373  OpID = 3;
3374  IID = isSigned ? llvm::Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow :
3375  llvm::Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow;
3376  OverflowKind = SanitizerHandler::MulOverflow;
3377  break;
3378  default:
3379  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported operation for overflow detection");
3380  }
3381  OpID <<= 1;
3382  if (isSigned)
3383  OpID |= 1;
3384 
3385  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
3386  llvm::Type *opTy = CGF.CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(Ops.Ty);
3387 
3388  llvm::Function *intrinsic = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(IID, opTy);
3389 
3390  Value *resultAndOverflow = Builder.CreateCall(intrinsic, {Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS});
3391  Value *result = Builder.CreateExtractValue(resultAndOverflow, 0);
3392  Value *overflow = Builder.CreateExtractValue(resultAndOverflow, 1);
3393 
3394  // Handle overflow with llvm.trap if no custom handler has been specified.
3395  const std::string *handlerName =
3396  &CGF.getLangOpts().OverflowHandler;
3397  if (handlerName->empty()) {
3398  // If the signed-integer-overflow sanitizer is enabled, emit a call to its
3399  // runtime. Otherwise, this is a -ftrapv check, so just emit a trap.
3400  if (!isSigned || CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow)) {
3401  llvm::Value *NotOverflow = Builder.CreateNot(overflow);
3402  SanitizerMask Kind = isSigned ? SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow
3403  : SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow;
3404  EmitBinOpCheck(std::make_pair(NotOverflow, Kind), Ops);
3405  } else
3406  CGF.EmitTrapCheck(Builder.CreateNot(overflow), OverflowKind);
3407  return result;
3408  }
3409 
3410  // Branch in case of overflow.
3411  llvm::BasicBlock *initialBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3412  llvm::BasicBlock *continueBB =
3413  CGF.createBasicBlock("nooverflow", CGF.CurFn, initialBB->getNextNode());
3414  llvm::BasicBlock *overflowBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("overflow", CGF.CurFn);
3415 
3416  Builder.CreateCondBr(overflow, overflowBB, continueBB);
3417 
3418  // If an overflow handler is set, then we want to call it and then use its
3419  // result, if it returns.
3420  Builder.SetInsertPoint(overflowBB);
3421 
3422  // Get the overflow handler.
3423  llvm::Type *Int8Ty = CGF.Int8Ty;
3424  llvm::Type *argTypes[] = { CGF.Int64Ty, CGF.Int64Ty, Int8Ty, Int8Ty };
3425  llvm::FunctionType *handlerTy =
3426  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.Int64Ty, argTypes, true);
3427  llvm::FunctionCallee handler =
3428  CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(handlerTy, *handlerName);
3429 
3430  // Sign extend the args to 64-bit, so that we can use the same handler for
3431  // all types of overflow.
3432  llvm::Value *lhs = Builder.CreateSExt(Ops.LHS, CGF.Int64Ty);
3433  llvm::Value *rhs = Builder.CreateSExt(Ops.RHS, CGF.Int64Ty);
3434 
3435  // Call the handler with the two arguments, the operation, and the size of
3436  // the result.
3437  llvm::Value *handlerArgs[] = {
3438  lhs,
3439  rhs,
3440  Builder.getInt8(OpID),
3441  Builder.getInt8(cast<llvm::IntegerType>(opTy)->getBitWidth())
3442  };
3443  llvm::Value *handlerResult =
3444  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(handler, handlerArgs);
3445 
3446  // Truncate the result back to the desired size.
3447  handlerResult = Builder.CreateTrunc(handlerResult, opTy);
3448  Builder.CreateBr(continueBB);
3449 
3450  Builder.SetInsertPoint(continueBB);
3451  llvm::PHINode *phi = Builder.CreatePHI(opTy, 2);
3452  phi->addIncoming(result, initialBB);
3453  phi->addIncoming(handlerResult, overflowBB);
3454 
3455  return phi;
3456 }
3457 
3458 /// Emit pointer + index arithmetic.
3459 static Value *emitPointerArithmetic(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3460  const BinOpInfo &op,
3461  bool isSubtraction) {
3462  // Must have binary (not unary) expr here. Unary pointer
3463  // increment/decrement doesn't use this path.
3464  const BinaryOperator *expr = cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E);
3465 
3466  Value *pointer = op.LHS;
3467  Expr *pointerOperand = expr->getLHS();
3468  Value *index = op.RHS;
3469  Expr *indexOperand = expr->getRHS();
3470 
3471  // In a subtraction, the LHS is always the pointer.
3472  if (!isSubtraction && !pointer->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
3473  std::swap(pointer, index);
3474  std::swap(pointerOperand, indexOperand);
3475  }
3476 
3477  bool isSigned = indexOperand->getType()->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
3478 
3479  unsigned width = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(index->getType())->getBitWidth();
3480  auto &DL = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout();
3481  auto PtrTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(pointer->getType());
3482 
3483  // Some versions of glibc and gcc use idioms (particularly in their malloc
3484  // routines) that add a pointer-sized integer (known to be a pointer value)
3485  // to a null pointer in order to cast the value back to an integer or as
3486  // part of a pointer alignment algorithm. This is undefined behavior, but
3487  // we'd like to be able to compile programs that use it.
3488  //
3489  // Normally, we'd generate a GEP with a null-pointer base here in response
3490  // to that code, but it's also UB to dereference a pointer created that
3491  // way. Instead (as an acknowledged hack to tolerate the idiom) we will
3492  // generate a direct cast of the integer value to a pointer.
3493  //
3494  // The idiom (p = nullptr + N) is not met if any of the following are true:
3495  //
3496  // The operation is subtraction.
3497  // The index is not pointer-sized.
3498  // The pointer type is not byte-sized.
3499  //
3500  if (BinaryOperator::isNullPointerArithmeticExtension(CGF.getContext(),
3501  op.Opcode,
3502  expr->getLHS(),
3503  expr->getRHS()))
3504  return CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(index, pointer->getType());
3505 
3506  if (width != DL.getIndexTypeSizeInBits(PtrTy)) {
3507  // Zero-extend or sign-extend the pointer value according to
3508  // whether the index is signed or not.
3509  index = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(index, DL.getIndexType(PtrTy), isSigned,
3510  "idx.ext");
3511  }
3512 
3513  // If this is subtraction, negate the index.
3514  if (isSubtraction)
3515  index = CGF.Builder.CreateNeg(index, "idx.neg");
3516 
3517  if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds))
3518  CGF.EmitBoundsCheck(op.E, pointerOperand, index, indexOperand->getType(),
3519  /*Accessed*/ false);
3520 
3521  const PointerType *pointerType
3522  = pointerOperand->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
3523  if (!pointerType) {
3524  QualType objectType = pointerOperand->getType()
3525  ->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()
3526  ->getPointeeType();
3527  llvm::Value *objectSize
3528  = CGF.CGM.getSize(CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(objectType));
3529 
3530  index = CGF.Builder.CreateMul(index, objectSize);
3531 
3532  Value *result = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(pointer, CGF.VoidPtrTy);
3533  result = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, result, index, "add.ptr");
3534  return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(result, pointer->getType());
3535  }
3536 
3537  QualType elementType = pointerType->getPointeeType();
3538  if (const VariableArrayType *vla
3539  = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(elementType)) {
3540  // The element count here is the total number of non-VLA elements.
3541  llvm::Value *numElements = CGF.getVLASize(vla).NumElts;
3542 
3543  // Effectively, the multiply by the VLA size is part of the GEP.
3544  // GEP indexes are signed, and scaling an index isn't permitted to
3545  // signed-overflow, so we use the same semantics for our explicit
3546  // multiply. We suppress this if overflow is not undefined behavior.
3547  llvm::Type *elemTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(vla->getElementType());
3548  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined()) {
3549  index = CGF.Builder.CreateMul(index, numElements, "vla.index");
3550  pointer = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(elemTy, pointer, index, "add.ptr");
3551  } else {
3552  index = CGF.Builder.CreateNSWMul(index, numElements, "vla.index");
3553  pointer = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
3554  elemTy, pointer, index, isSigned, isSubtraction, op.E->getExprLoc(),
3555  "add.ptr");
3556  }
3557  return pointer;
3558  }
3559 
3560  // Explicitly handle GNU void* and function pointer arithmetic extensions. The
3561  // GNU void* casts amount to no-ops since our void* type is i8*, but this is
3562  // future proof.
3563  if (elementType->isVoidType() || elementType->isFunctionType()) {
3564  Value *result = CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(pointer);
3565  result = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, result, index, "add.ptr");
3566  return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(result, pointer->getType());
3567  }
3568 
3569  llvm::Type *elemTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(elementType);
3570  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
3571  return CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(elemTy, pointer, index, "add.ptr");
3572 
3573  return CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
3574  elemTy, pointer, index, isSigned, isSubtraction, op.E->getExprLoc(),
3575  "add.ptr");
3576 }
3577 
3578 // Construct an fmuladd intrinsic to represent a fused mul-add of MulOp and
3579 // Addend. Use negMul and negAdd to negate the first operand of the Mul or
3580 // the add operand respectively. This allows fmuladd to represent a*b-c, or
3581 // c-a*b. Patterns in LLVM should catch the negated forms and translate them to
3582 // efficient operations.
3583 static Value* buildFMulAdd(llvm::Instruction *MulOp, Value *Addend,
3584  const CodeGenFunction &CGF, CGBuilderTy &Builder,
3585  bool negMul, bool negAdd) {
3586  assert(!(negMul && negAdd) && "Only one of negMul and negAdd should be set.");
3587 
3588  Value *MulOp0 = MulOp->getOperand(0);
3589  Value *MulOp1 = MulOp->getOperand(1);
3590  if (negMul)
3591  MulOp0 = Builder.CreateFNeg(MulOp0, "neg");
3592  if (negAdd)
3593  Addend = Builder.CreateFNeg(Addend, "neg");
3594 
3595  Value *FMulAdd = nullptr;
3596  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
3597  assert(isa<llvm::ConstrainedFPIntrinsic>(MulOp) &&
3598  "Only constrained operation should be created when Builder is in FP "
3599  "constrained mode");
3600  FMulAdd = Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(
3601  CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fmuladd,
3602  Addend->getType()),
3603  {MulOp0, MulOp1, Addend});
3604  } else {
3605  FMulAdd = Builder.CreateCall(
3606  CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::fmuladd, Addend->getType()),
3607  {MulOp0, MulOp1, Addend});
3608  }
3609  MulOp->eraseFromParent();
3610 
3611  return FMulAdd;
3612 }
3613 
3614 // Check whether it would be legal to emit an fmuladd intrinsic call to
3615 // represent op and if so, build the fmuladd.
3616 //
3617 // Checks that (a) the operation is fusable, and (b) -ffp-contract=on.
3618 // Does NOT check the type of the operation - it's assumed that this function
3619 // will be called from contexts where it's known that the type is contractable.
3620 static Value* tryEmitFMulAdd(const BinOpInfo &op,
3621  const CodeGenFunction &CGF, CGBuilderTy &Builder,
3622  bool isSub=false) {
3623 
3624  assert((op.Opcode == BO_Add || op.Opcode == BO_AddAssign ||
3625  op.Opcode == BO_Sub || op.Opcode == BO_SubAssign) &&
3626  "Only fadd/fsub can be the root of an fmuladd.");
3627 
3628  // Check whether this op is marked as fusable.
3629  if (!op.FPFeatures.allowFPContractWithinStatement())
3630  return nullptr;
3631 
3632  // We have a potentially fusable op. Look for a mul on one of the operands.
3633  // Also, make sure that the mul result isn't used directly. In that case,
3634  // there's no point creating a muladd operation.
3635  if (auto *LHSBinOp = dyn_cast<llvm::BinaryOperator>(op.LHS)) {
3636  if (LHSBinOp->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::FMul &&
3637  LHSBinOp->use_empty())
3638  return buildFMulAdd(LHSBinOp, op.RHS, CGF, Builder, false, isSub);
3639  }
3640  if (auto *RHSBinOp = dyn_cast<llvm::BinaryOperator>(op.RHS)) {
3641  if (RHSBinOp->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::FMul &&
3642  RHSBinOp->use_empty())
3643  return buildFMulAdd(RHSBinOp, op.LHS, CGF, Builder, isSub, false);
3644  }
3645 
3646  if (auto *LHSBinOp = dyn_cast<llvm::CallBase>(op.LHS)) {
3647  if (LHSBinOp->getIntrinsicID() ==
3648  llvm::Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fmul &&
3649  LHSBinOp->use_empty())
3650  return buildFMulAdd(LHSBinOp, op.RHS, CGF, Builder, false, isSub);
3651  }
3652  if (auto *RHSBinOp = dyn_cast<llvm::CallBase>(op.RHS)) {
3653  if (RHSBinOp->getIntrinsicID() ==
3654  llvm::Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fmul &&
3655  RHSBinOp->use_empty())
3656  return buildFMulAdd(RHSBinOp, op.LHS, CGF, Builder, isSub, false);
3657  }
3658 
3659  return nullptr;
3660 }
3661 
3662 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitAdd(const BinOpInfo &op) {
3663  if (op.LHS->getType()->isPointerTy() ||
3664  op.RHS->getType()->isPointerTy())
3665  return emitPointerArithmetic(CGF, op, CodeGenFunction::NotSubtraction);
3666 
3667  if (op.Ty->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) {
3668  switch (CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior()) {
3669  case LangOptions::SOB_Defined:
3670  return Builder.CreateAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
3671  case LangOptions::SOB_Undefined:
3672  if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
3673  return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
3674  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3675  case LangOptions::SOB_Trapping:
3676  if (CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
3677  return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
3678  return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
3679  }
3680  }
3681 
3682  if (op.Ty->isConstantMatrixType()) {
3683  llvm::MatrixBuilder MB(Builder);
3684  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, op.FPFeatures);
3685  return MB.CreateAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS);
3686  }
3687 
3688  if (op.Ty->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
3689  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow) &&
3690  !CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
3691  return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
3692 
3693  if (op.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
3694  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, op.FPFeatures);
3695  // Try to form an fmuladd.
3696  if (Value *FMulAdd = tryEmitFMulAdd(op, CGF, Builder))
3697  return FMulAdd;
3698 
3699  return Builder.CreateFAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
3700  }
3701 
3702  if (op.isFixedPointOp())
3703  return EmitFixedPointBinOp(op);
3704 
3705  return Builder.CreateAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
3706 }
3707 
3708 /// The resulting value must be calculated with exact precision, so the operands
3709 /// may not be the same type.
3710 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitFixedPointBinOp(const BinOpInfo &op) {
3711  using llvm::APSInt;
3712  using llvm::ConstantInt;
3713 
3714  // This is either a binary operation where at least one of the operands is
3715  // a fixed-point type, or a unary operation where the operand is a fixed-point
3716  // type. The result type of a binary operation is determined by
3717  // Sema::handleFixedPointConversions().
3718  QualType ResultTy = op.Ty;
3719  QualType LHSTy, RHSTy;
3720  if (const auto *BinOp = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E)) {
3721  RHSTy = BinOp->getRHS()->getType();
3722  if (const auto *CAO = dyn_cast<CompoundAssignOperator>(BinOp)) {
3723  // For compound assignment, the effective type of the LHS at this point
3724  // is the computation LHS type, not the actual LHS type, and the final
3725  // result type is not the type of the expression but rather the
3726  // computation result type.
3727  LHSTy = CAO->getComputationLHSType();
3728  ResultTy = CAO->getComputationResultType();
3729  } else
3730  LHSTy = BinOp->getLHS()->getType();
3731  } else if (const auto *UnOp = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(op.E)) {
3732  LHSTy = UnOp->getSubExpr()->getType();
3733  RHSTy = UnOp->getSubExpr()->getType();
3734  }
3735  ASTContext &Ctx = CGF.getContext();
3736  Value *LHS = op.LHS;
3737  Value *RHS = op.RHS;
3738 
3739  auto LHSFixedSema = Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(LHSTy);
3740  auto RHSFixedSema = Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(RHSTy);
3741  auto ResultFixedSema = Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(ResultTy);
3742  auto CommonFixedSema = LHSFixedSema.getCommonSemantics(RHSFixedSema);
3743 
3744  // Perform the actual operation.
3745  Value *Result;
3746  llvm::FixedPointBuilder<CGBuilderTy> FPBuilder(Builder);
3747  switch (op.Opcode) {
3748  case BO_AddAssign:
3749  case BO_Add:
3750  Result = FPBuilder.CreateAdd(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
3751  break;
3752  case BO_SubAssign:
3753  case BO_Sub:
3754  Result = FPBuilder.CreateSub(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
3755  break;
3756  case BO_MulAssign:
3757  case BO_Mul:
3758  Result = FPBuilder.CreateMul(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
3759  break;
3760  case BO_DivAssign:
3761  case BO_Div:
3762  Result = FPBuilder.CreateDiv(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
3763  break;
3764  case BO_ShlAssign:
3765  case BO_Shl:
3766  Result = FPBuilder.CreateShl(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS);
3767  break;
3768  case BO_ShrAssign:
3769  case BO_Shr:
3770  Result = FPBuilder.CreateShr(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS);
3771  break;
3772  case BO_LT:
3773  return FPBuilder.CreateLT(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
3774  case BO_GT:
3775  return FPBuilder.CreateGT(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
3776  case BO_LE:
3777  return FPBuilder.CreateLE(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
3778  case BO_GE:
3779  return FPBuilder.CreateGE(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
3780  case BO_EQ:
3781  // For equality operations, we assume any padding bits on unsigned types are
3782  // zero'd out. They could be overwritten through non-saturating operations
3783  // that cause overflow, but this leads to undefined behavior.
3784  return FPBuilder.CreateEQ(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
3785  case BO_NE:
3786  return FPBuilder.CreateNE(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
3787  case BO_Cmp:
3788  case BO_LAnd:
3789  case BO_LOr:
3790  llvm_unreachable("Found unimplemented fixed point binary operation");
3791  case BO_PtrMemD:
3792  case BO_PtrMemI:
3793  case BO_Rem:
3794  case BO_Xor:
3795  case BO_And:
3796  case BO_Or:
3797  case BO_Assign:
3798  case BO_RemAssign:
3799  case BO_AndAssign:
3800  case BO_XorAssign:
3801  case BO_OrAssign:
3802  case BO_Comma:
3803  llvm_unreachable("Found unsupported binary operation for fixed point types.");
3804  }
3805 
3806  bool IsShift = BinaryOperator::isShiftOp(op.Opcode) ||
3807  BinaryOperator::isShiftAssignOp(op.Opcode);
3808  // Convert to the result type.
3809  return FPBuilder.CreateFixedToFixed(Result, IsShift ? LHSFixedSema
3810  : CommonFixedSema,
3811  ResultFixedSema);
3812 }
3813 
3814 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitSub(const BinOpInfo &op) {
3815  // The LHS is always a pointer if either side is.
3816  if (!op.LHS->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
3817  if (op.Ty->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) {
3818  switch (CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior()) {
3819  case LangOptions::SOB_Defined:
3820  return Builder.CreateSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
3821  case LangOptions::SOB_Undefined:
3822  if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
3823  return Builder.CreateNSWSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
3824  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3825  case LangOptions::SOB_Trapping:
3826  if (CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
3827  return Builder.CreateNSWSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
3828  return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
3829  }
3830  }
3831 
3832  if (op.Ty->isConstantMatrixType()) {
3833  llvm::MatrixBuilder MB(Builder);
3834  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, op.FPFeatures);
3835  return MB.CreateSub(op.LHS, op.RHS);
3836  }
3837 
3838  if (op.Ty->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
3839  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow) &&
3840  !CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
3841  return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
3842 
3843  if (op.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
3844  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, op.FPFeatures);
3845  // Try to form an fmuladd.
3846  if (Value *FMulAdd = tryEmitFMulAdd(op, CGF, Builder, true))
3847  return FMulAdd;
3848  return Builder.CreateFSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
3849  }
3850 
3851  if (op.isFixedPointOp())
3852  return EmitFixedPointBinOp(op);
3853 
3854  return Builder.CreateSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
3855  }
3856 
3857  // If the RHS is not a pointer, then we have normal pointer
3858  // arithmetic.
3859  if (!op.RHS->getType()->isPointerTy())
3860  return emitPointerArithmetic(CGF, op, CodeGenFunction::IsSubtraction);
3861 
3862  // Otherwise, this is a pointer subtraction.
3863 
3864  // Do the raw subtraction part.
3865  llvm::Value *LHS
3866  = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(op.LHS, CGF.PtrDiffTy, "sub.ptr.lhs.cast");
3867  llvm::Value *RHS
3868  = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(op.RHS, CGF.PtrDiffTy, "sub.ptr.rhs.cast");
3869  Value *diffInChars = Builder.CreateSub(LHS, RHS, "sub.ptr.sub");
3870 
3871  // Okay, figure out the element size.
3872  const BinaryOperator *expr = cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E);
3873  QualType elementType = expr->getLHS()->getType()->getPointeeType();
3874 
3875  llvm::Value *divisor = nullptr;
3876 
3877  // For a variable-length array, this is going to be non-constant.
3878  if (const VariableArrayType *vla
3879  = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(elementType)) {
3880  auto VlaSize = CGF.getVLASize(vla);
3881  elementType = VlaSize.Type;
3882  divisor = VlaSize.NumElts;
3883 
3884  // Scale the number of non-VLA elements by the non-VLA element size.
3885  CharUnits eltSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(elementType);
3886  if (!eltSize.isOne())
3887  divisor = CGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(CGF.CGM.getSize(eltSize), divisor);
3888 
3889  // For everything elese, we can just compute it, safe in the
3890  // assumption that Sema won't let anything through that we can't
3891  // safely compute the size of.
3892  } else {
3893  CharUnits elementSize;
3894  // Handle GCC extension for pointer arithmetic on void* and
3895  // function pointer types.
3896  if (elementType->isVoidType() || elementType->isFunctionType())
3897  elementSize = CharUnits::One();
3898  else
3899  elementSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(elementType);
3900 
3901  // Don't even emit the divide for element size of 1.
3902  if (elementSize.isOne())
3903  return diffInChars;
3904 
3905  divisor = CGF.CGM.getSize(elementSize);
3906  }
3907 
3908  // Otherwise, do a full sdiv. This uses the "exact" form of sdiv, since
3909  // pointer difference in C is only defined in the case where both operands
3910  // are pointing to elements of an array.
3911  return Builder.CreateExactSDiv(diffInChars, divisor, "sub.ptr.div");
3912 }
3913 
3914 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::GetWidthMinusOneValue(Value* LHS,Value* RHS) {
3915  llvm::IntegerType *Ty;
3916  if (llvm::VectorType *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(LHS->getType()))
3917  Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(VT->getElementType());
3918  else
3919  Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(LHS->getType());
3920  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(RHS->getType(), Ty->getBitWidth() - 1);
3921 }
3922 
3923 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::ConstrainShiftValue(Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
3924  const Twine &Name) {
3925  llvm::IntegerType *Ty;
3926  if (auto *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(LHS->getType()))
3927  Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(VT->getElementType());
3928  else
3929  Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(LHS->getType());
3930 
3931  if (llvm::isPowerOf2_64(Ty->getBitWidth()))
3932  return Builder.CreateAnd(RHS, GetWidthMinusOneValue(LHS, RHS), Name);
3933 
3934  return Builder.CreateURem(
3935  RHS, llvm::ConstantInt::get(RHS->getType(), Ty->getBitWidth()), Name);
3936 }
3937 
3938 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitShl(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
3939  // TODO: This misses out on the sanitizer check below.
3940  if (Ops.isFixedPointOp())
3941  return EmitFixedPointBinOp(Ops);
3942 
3943  // LLVM requires the LHS and RHS to be the same type: promote or truncate the
3944  // RHS to the same size as the LHS.
3945  Value *RHS = Ops.RHS;
3946  if (Ops.LHS->getType() != RHS->getType())
3947  RHS = Builder.CreateIntCast(RHS, Ops.LHS->getType(), false, "sh_prom");
3948 
3949  bool SanitizeSignedBase = CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ShiftBase) &&
3950  Ops.Ty->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation() &&
3951  !CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined() &&
3952  !CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20;
3953  bool SanitizeUnsignedBase =
3954  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedShiftBase) &&
3955  Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation();
3956  bool SanitizeBase = SanitizeSignedBase || SanitizeUnsignedBase;
3957  bool SanitizeExponent = CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent);
3958  // OpenCL 6.3j: shift values are effectively % word size of LHS.
3959  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
3960  RHS = ConstrainShiftValue(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shl.mask");
3961  else if ((SanitizeBase || SanitizeExponent) &&
3962  isa<llvm::IntegerType>(Ops.LHS->getType())) {
3963  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
3964  SmallVector<std::pair<Value *, SanitizerMask>, 2> Checks;
3965  llvm::Value *WidthMinusOne = GetWidthMinusOneValue(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS);
3966  llvm::Value *ValidExponent = Builder.CreateICmpULE(Ops.RHS, WidthMinusOne);
3967 
3968  if (SanitizeExponent) {
3969  Checks.push_back(
3970  std::make_pair(ValidExponent, SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent));
3971  }
3972 
3973  if (SanitizeBase) {
3974  // Check whether we are shifting any non-zero bits off the top of the
3975  // integer. We only emit this check if exponent is valid - otherwise
3976  // instructions below will have undefined behavior themselves.
3977  llvm::BasicBlock *Orig = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3978  llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = CGF.createBasicBlock("cont");
3979  llvm::BasicBlock *CheckShiftBase = CGF.createBasicBlock("check");
3980  Builder.CreateCondBr(ValidExponent, CheckShiftBase, Cont);
3981  llvm::Value *PromotedWidthMinusOne =
3982  (RHS == Ops.RHS) ? WidthMinusOne
3983  : GetWidthMinusOneValue(Ops.LHS, RHS);
3984  CGF.EmitBlock(CheckShiftBase);
3985  llvm::Value *BitsShiftedOff = Builder.CreateLShr(
3986  Ops.LHS, Builder.CreateSub(PromotedWidthMinusOne, RHS, "shl.zeros",
3987  /*NUW*/ true, /*NSW*/ true),
3988  "shl.check");
3989  if (SanitizeUnsignedBase || CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
3990  // In C99, we are not permitted to shift a 1 bit into the sign bit.
3991  // Under C++11's rules, shifting a 1 bit into the sign bit is
3992  // OK, but shifting a 1 bit out of it is not. (C89 and C++03 don't
3993  // define signed left shifts, so we use the C99 and C++11 rules there).
3994  // Unsigned shifts can always shift into the top bit.
3995  llvm::Value *One = llvm::ConstantInt::get(BitsShiftedOff->getType(), 1);
3996  BitsShiftedOff = Builder.CreateLShr(BitsShiftedOff, One);
3997  }
3998  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(BitsShiftedOff->getType(), 0);
3999  llvm::Value *ValidBase = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(BitsShiftedOff, Zero);
4000  CGF.EmitBlock(Cont);
4001  llvm::PHINode *BaseCheck = Builder.CreatePHI(ValidBase->getType(), 2);
4002  BaseCheck->addIncoming(Builder.getTrue(), Orig);
4003  BaseCheck->addIncoming(ValidBase, CheckShiftBase);
4004  Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(
4005  BaseCheck, SanitizeSignedBase ? SanitizerKind::ShiftBase
4006  : SanitizerKind::UnsignedShiftBase));
4007  }
4008 
4009  assert(!Checks.empty());
4010  EmitBinOpCheck(Checks, Ops);
4011  }
4012 
4013  return Builder.CreateShl(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shl");
4014 }
4015 
4016 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitShr(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
4017  // TODO: This misses out on the sanitizer check below.
4018  if (Ops.isFixedPointOp())
4019  return EmitFixedPointBinOp(Ops);
4020 
4021  // LLVM requires the LHS and RHS to be the same type: promote or truncate the
4022  // RHS to the same size as the LHS.
4023  Value *RHS = Ops.RHS;
4024  if (Ops.LHS->getType() != RHS->getType())
4025  RHS = Builder.CreateIntCast(RHS, Ops.LHS->getType(), false, "sh_prom");
4026 
4027  // OpenCL 6.3j: shift values are effectively % word size of LHS.
4028  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
4029  RHS = ConstrainShiftValue(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shr.mask");
4030  else if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent) &&
4031  isa<llvm::IntegerType>(Ops.LHS->getType())) {
4032  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
4033  llvm::Value *Valid =
4034  Builder.CreateICmpULE(RHS, GetWidthMinusOneValue(Ops.LHS, RHS));
4035  EmitBinOpCheck(std::make_pair(Valid, SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent), Ops);
4036  }
4037 
4038  if (Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation())
4039  return Builder.CreateLShr(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shr");
4040  return Builder.CreateAShr(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shr");
4041 }
4042 
4043 enum IntrinsicType { VCMPEQ, VCMPGT };
4044 // return corresponding comparison intrinsic for given vector type
4045 static llvm::Intrinsic::ID GetIntrinsic(IntrinsicType IT,
4046  BuiltinType::Kind ElemKind) {
4047  switch (ElemKind) {
4048  default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected element type");
4049  case BuiltinType::Char_U:
4050  case BuiltinType::UChar:
4051  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequb_p :
4052  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtub_p;
4053  case BuiltinType::Char_S:
4054  case BuiltinType::SChar:
4055  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequb_p :
4056  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsb_p;
4057  case BuiltinType::UShort:
4058  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequh_p :
4059  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtuh_p;
4060  case BuiltinType::Short:
4061  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequh_p :
4062  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsh_p;
4063  case BuiltinType::UInt:
4064  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequw_p :
4065  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtuw_p;
4066  case BuiltinType::Int:
4067  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequw_p :
4068  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsw_p;
4069  case BuiltinType::ULong:
4070  case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
4071  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequd_p :
4072  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtud_p;
4073  case BuiltinType::Long:
4074  case BuiltinType::LongLong:
4075  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequd_p :
4076  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsd_p;
4077  case BuiltinType::Float:
4078  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpeqfp_p :
4079  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtfp_p;
4080  case BuiltinType::Double:
4081  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_xvcmpeqdp_p :
4082  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_xvcmpgtdp_p;
4083  case BuiltinType::UInt128:
4084  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequq_p
4085  : llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtuq_p;
4086  case BuiltinType::Int128:
4087  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequq_p
4088  : llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsq_p;
4089  }
4090 }
4091 
4092 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitCompare(const BinaryOperator *E,
4093  llvm::CmpInst::Predicate UICmpOpc,
4094  llvm::CmpInst::Predicate SICmpOpc,
4095  llvm::CmpInst::Predicate FCmpOpc,
4096  bool IsSignaling) {
4097  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
4098  Value *Result;
4099  QualType LHSTy = E->getLHS()->getType();
4100  QualType RHSTy = E->getRHS()->getType();
4101  if (const MemberPointerType *MPT = LHSTy->getAs<MemberPointerType>()) {
4102  assert(E->getOpcode() == BO_EQ ||
4103  E->getOpcode() == BO_NE);
4104  Value *LHS = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getLHS());
4105  Value *RHS = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getRHS());
4106  Result = CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerComparison(
4107  CGF, LHS, RHS, MPT, E->getOpcode() == BO_NE);
4108  } else if (!LHSTy->isAnyComplexType() && !RHSTy->isAnyComplexType()) {
4109  BinOpInfo BOInfo = EmitBinOps(E);
4110  Value *LHS = BOInfo.LHS;
4111  Value *RHS = BOInfo.RHS;
4112 
4113  // If AltiVec, the comparison results in a numeric type, so we use
4114  // intrinsics comparing vectors and giving 0 or 1 as a result
4115  if (LHSTy->isVectorType() && !E->getType()->isVectorType()) {
4116  // constants for mapping CR6 register bits to predicate result
4117  enum { CR6_EQ=0, CR6_EQ_REV, CR6_LT, CR6_LT_REV } CR6;
4118 
4119  llvm::Intrinsic::ID ID = llvm::Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
4120 
4121  // in several cases vector arguments order will be reversed
4122  Value *FirstVecArg = LHS,
4123  *SecondVecArg = RHS;
4124 
4125  QualType ElTy = LHSTy->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
4126  BuiltinType::Kind ElementKind = ElTy->castAs<BuiltinType>()->getKind();
4127 
4128  switch(E->getOpcode()) {
4129  default: llvm_unreachable("is not a comparison operation");
4130  case BO_EQ:
4131  CR6 = CR6_LT;
4132  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPEQ, ElementKind);
4133  break;
4134  case BO_NE:
4135  CR6 = CR6_EQ;
4136  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPEQ, ElementKind);
4137  break;
4138  case BO_LT:
4139  CR6 = CR6_LT;
4140  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4141  std::swap(FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg);
4142  break;
4143  case BO_GT:
4144  CR6 = CR6_LT;
4145  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4146  break;
4147  case BO_LE:
4148  if (ElementKind == BuiltinType::Float) {
4149  CR6 = CR6_LT;
4150  ID = llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgefp_p;
4151  std::swap(FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg);
4152  }
4153  else {
4154  CR6 = CR6_EQ;
4155  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4156  }
4157  break;
4158  case BO_GE:
4159  if (ElementKind == BuiltinType::Float) {
4160  CR6 = CR6_LT;
4161  ID = llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgefp_p;
4162  }
4163  else {
4164  CR6 = CR6_EQ;
4165  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4166  std::swap(FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg);
4167  }
4168  break;
4169  }
4170 
4171  Value *CR6Param = Builder.getInt32(CR6);
4172  llvm::Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(ID);
4173  Result = Builder.CreateCall(F, {CR6Param, FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg});
4174 
4175  // The result type of intrinsic may not be same as E->getType().
4176  // If E->getType() is not BoolTy, EmitScalarConversion will do the
4177  // conversion work. If E->getType() is BoolTy, EmitScalarConversion will
4178  // do nothing, if ResultTy is not i1 at the same time, it will cause
4179  // crash later.
4180  llvm::IntegerType *ResultTy = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Result->getType());
4181  if (ResultTy->getBitWidth() > 1 &&
4182  E->getType() == CGF.getContext().BoolTy)
4183  Result = Builder.CreateTrunc(Result, Builder.getInt1Ty());
4184  return EmitScalarConversion(Result, CGF.getContext().BoolTy, E->getType(),
4185  E->getExprLoc());
4186  }
4187 
4188  if (BOInfo.isFixedPointOp()) {
4189  Result = EmitFixedPointBinOp(BOInfo);
4190  } else if (LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4191  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, BOInfo.FPFeatures);
4192  if (!IsSignaling)
4193  Result = Builder.CreateFCmp(FCmpOpc, LHS, RHS, "cmp");
4194  else
4195  Result = Builder.CreateFCmpS(FCmpOpc, LHS, RHS, "cmp");
4196  } else if (LHSTy->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation()) {
4197  Result = Builder.CreateICmp(SICmpOpc, LHS, RHS, "cmp");
4198  } else {
4199  // Unsigned integers and pointers.
4200 
4201  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
4202  !isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(LHS) &&
4203  !isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(RHS)) {
4204 
4205  // Dynamic information is required to be stripped for comparisons,
4206  // because it could leak the dynamic information. Based on comparisons
4207  // of pointers to dynamic objects, the optimizer can replace one pointer
4208  // with another, which might be incorrect in presence of invariant
4209  // groups. Comparison with null is safe because null does not carry any
4210  // dynamic information.
4211  if (LHSTy.mayBeDynamicClass())
4212  LHS = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(LHS);
4213  if (RHSTy.mayBeDynamicClass())
4214  RHS = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(RHS);
4215  }
4216 
4217  Result = Builder.CreateICmp(UICmpOpc, LHS, RHS, "cmp");
4218  }
4219 
4220  // If this is a vector comparison, sign extend the result to the appropriate
4221  // vector integer type and return it (don't convert to bool).
4222  if (LHSTy->isVectorType())
4223  return Builder.CreateSExt(Result, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
4224 
4225  } else {
4226  // Complex Comparison: can only be an equality comparison.
4227  CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy LHS, RHS;
4228  QualType CETy;
4229  if (auto *CTy = LHSTy->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
4230  LHS = CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E->getLHS());
4231  CETy = CTy->getElementType();
4232  } else {
4233  LHS.first = Visit(E->getLHS());
4234  LHS.second = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(LHS.first->getType());
4235  CETy = LHSTy;
4236  }
4237  if (auto *CTy = RHSTy->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
4238  RHS = CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E->getRHS());
4239  assert(CGF.getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType(CETy,
4240  CTy->getElementType()) &&
4241  "The element types must always match.");
4242  (void)CTy;
4243  } else {
4244  RHS.first = Visit(E->getRHS());
4245  RHS.second = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(RHS.first->getType());
4246  assert(CGF.getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType(CETy, RHSTy) &&
4247  "The element types must always match.");
4248  }
4249 
4250  Value *ResultR, *ResultI;
4251  if (CETy->isRealFloatingType()) {
4252  // As complex comparisons can only be equality comparisons, they
4253  // are never signaling comparisons.
4254  ResultR = Builder.CreateFCmp(FCmpOpc, LHS.first, RHS.first, "cmp.r");
4255  ResultI = Builder.CreateFCmp(FCmpOpc, LHS.second, RHS.second, "cmp.i");
4256  } else {
4257  // Complex comparisons can only be equality comparisons. As such, signed
4258  // and unsigned opcodes are the same.
4259  ResultR = Builder.CreateICmp(UICmpOpc, LHS.first, RHS.first, "cmp.r");
4260  ResultI = Builder.CreateICmp(UICmpOpc, LHS.second, RHS.second, "cmp.i");
4261  }
4262 
4263  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_EQ) {
4264  Result = Builder.CreateAnd(ResultR, ResultI, "and.ri");
4265  } else {
4266  assert(E->getOpcode() == BO_NE &&
4267  "Complex comparison other than == or != ?");
4268  Result = Builder.CreateOr(ResultR, ResultI, "or.ri");
4269  }
4270  }
4271 
4272  return EmitScalarConversion(Result, CGF.getContext().BoolTy, E->getType(),
4273  E->getExprLoc());
4274 }
4275 
4276 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinAssign(const BinaryOperator *E) {
4277  bool Ignore = TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
4278 
4279  Value *RHS;
4280  LValue LHS;
4281 
4282  switch (E->getLHS()->getType().getObjCLifetime()) {
4283  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
4284  std::tie(LHS, RHS) = CGF.EmitARCStoreStrong(E, Ignore);
4285  break;
4286 
4287  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
4288  std::tie(LHS, RHS) = CGF.EmitARCStoreAutoreleasing(E);
4289  break;
4290 
4291  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
4292  std::tie(LHS, RHS) = CGF.EmitARCStoreUnsafeUnretained(E, Ignore);
4293  break;
4294 
4295  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
4296  RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4297  LHS = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), CodeGenFunction::TCK_Store);
4298  RHS = CGF.EmitARCStoreWeak(LHS.getAddress(CGF), RHS, Ignore);
4299  break;
4300 
4301  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
4302  // __block variables need to have the rhs evaluated first, plus
4303  // this should improve codegen just a little.
4304  RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4305  LHS = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), CodeGenFunction::TCK_Store);
4306 
4307  // Store the value into the LHS. Bit-fields are handled specially
4308  // because the result is altered by the store, i.e., [C99 6.5.16p1]
4309  // 'An assignment expression has the value of the left operand after
4310  // the assignment...'.
4311  if (LHS.isBitField()) {
4312  CGF.EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue::get(RHS), LHS, &RHS);
4313  } else {
4314  CGF.EmitNullabilityCheck(LHS, RHS, E->getExprLoc());
4315  CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(RHS), LHS);
4316  }
4317  }
4318 
4319  // If the result is clearly ignored, return now.
4320  if (Ignore)
4321  return nullptr;
4322 
4323  // The result of an assignment in C is the assigned r-value.
4324  if (!CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
4325  return RHS;
4326 
4327  // If the lvalue is non-volatile, return the computed value of the assignment.
4328  if (!LHS.isVolatileQualified())
4329  return RHS;
4330 
4331  // Otherwise, reload the value.
4332  return EmitLoadOfLValue(LHS, E->getExprLoc());
4333 }
4334 
4335 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinLAnd(const BinaryOperator *E) {
4336  // Perform vector logical and on comparisons with zero vectors.
4337  if (E->getType()->isVectorType()) {
4338  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4339 
4340  Value *LHS = Visit(E->getLHS());
4341  Value *RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4342  Value *Zero = llvm::ConstantAggregateZero::get(LHS->getType());
4343  if (LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4344  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(
4345  CGF, E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts()));
4346  LHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
4347  RHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
4348  } else {
4349  LHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
4350  RHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
4351  }
4352  Value *And = Builder.CreateAnd(LHS, RHS);
4353  return Builder.CreateSExt(And, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
4354  }
4355 
4356  bool InstrumentRegions = CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasProfileClangInstr();
4357  llvm::Type *ResTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
4358 
4359  // If we have 0 && RHS, see if we can elide RHS, if so, just return 0.
4360  // If we have 1 && X, just emit X without inserting the control flow.
4361  bool LHSCondVal;
4362  if (CGF.ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(E->getLHS(), LHSCondVal)) {
4363  if (LHSCondVal) { // If we have 1 && X, just emit X.
4364  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4365 
4366  Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
4367 
4368  // If we're generating for profiling or coverage, generate a branch to a
4369  // block that increments the RHS counter needed to track branch condition
4370  // coverage. In this case, use "FBlock" as both the final "TrueBlock" and
4371  // "FalseBlock" after the increment is done.
4372  if (InstrumentRegions &&
4373  CodeGenFunction::isInstrumentedCondition(E->getRHS())) {
4374  llvm::BasicBlock *FBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.end");
4375  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlockCnt = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.rhscnt");
4376  Builder.CreateCondBr(RHSCond, RHSBlockCnt, FBlock);
4377  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlockCnt);
4378  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E->getRHS());
4379  CGF.EmitBranch(FBlock);
4380  CGF.EmitBlock(FBlock);
4381  }
4382 
4383  // ZExt result to int or bool.
4384  return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(RHSCond, ResTy, "land.ext");
4385  }
4386 
4387  // 0 && RHS: If it is safe, just elide the RHS, and return 0/false.
4388  if (!CGF.ContainsLabel(E->getRHS()))
4389  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ResTy);
4390  }
4391 
4392  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.end");
4393  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.rhs");
4394 
4395  CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation eval(CGF);
4396 
4397  // Branch on the LHS first. If it is false, go to the failure (cont) block.
4398  CGF.EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(E->getLHS(), RHSBlock, ContBlock,
4399  CGF.getProfileCount(E->getRHS()));
4400 
4401  // Any edges into the ContBlock are now from an (indeterminate number of)
4402  // edges from this first condition. All of these values will be false. Start
4403  // setting up the PHI node in the Cont Block for this.
4404  llvm::PHINode *PN = llvm::PHINode::Create(llvm::Type::getInt1Ty(VMContext), 2,
4405  "", ContBlock);
4406  for (llvm::pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(ContBlock), PE = pred_end(ContBlock);
4407  PI != PE; ++PI)
4408  PN->addIncoming(llvm::ConstantInt::getFalse(VMContext), *PI);
4409 
4410  eval.begin(CGF);
4411  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlock);
4412  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4413  Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
4414  eval.end(CGF);
4415 
4416  // Reaquire the RHS block, as there may be subblocks inserted.
4417  RHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4418 
4419  // If we're generating for profiling or coverage, generate a branch on the
4420  // RHS to a block that increments the RHS true counter needed to track branch
4421  // condition coverage.
4422  if (InstrumentRegions &&
4423  CodeGenFunction::isInstrumentedCondition(E->getRHS())) {
4424  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlockCnt = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.rhscnt");
4425  Builder.CreateCondBr(RHSCond, RHSBlockCnt, ContBlock);
4426  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlockCnt);
4427  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E->getRHS());
4428  CGF.EmitBranch(ContBlock);
4429  PN->addIncoming(RHSCond, RHSBlockCnt);
4430  }
4431 
4432  // Emit an unconditional branch from this block to ContBlock.
4433  {
4434  // There is no need to emit line number for unconditional branch.
4435  auto NL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateEmpty(CGF);
4436  CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
4437  }
4438  // Insert an entry into the phi node for the edge with the value of RHSCond.
4439  PN->addIncoming(RHSCond, RHSBlock);
4440 
4441  // Artificial location to preserve the scope information
4442  {
4443  auto NL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateArtificial(CGF);
4444  PN->setDebugLoc(Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation());
4445  }
4446 
4447  // ZExt result to int.
4448  return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(PN, ResTy, "land.ext");
4449 }
4450 
4451 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinLOr(const BinaryOperator *E) {
4452  // Perform vector logical or on comparisons with zero vectors.
4453  if (E->getType()->isVectorType()) {
4454  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4455 
4456  Value *LHS = Visit(E->getLHS());
4457  Value *RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4458  Value *Zero = llvm::ConstantAggregateZero::get(LHS->getType());
4459  if (LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4460  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(
4461  CGF, E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts()));
4462  LHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
4463  RHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
4464  } else {
4465  LHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
4466  RHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
4467  }
4468  Value *Or = Builder.CreateOr(LHS, RHS);
4469  return Builder.CreateSExt(Or, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
4470  }
4471 
4472  bool InstrumentRegions = CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasProfileClangInstr();
4473  llvm::Type *ResTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
4474 
4475  // If we have 1 || RHS, see if we can elide RHS, if so, just return 1.
4476  // If we have 0 || X, just emit X without inserting the control flow.
4477  bool LHSCondVal;
4478  if (CGF.ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(E->getLHS(), LHSCondVal)) {
4479  if (!LHSCondVal) { // If we have 0 || X, just emit X.
4480  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4481 
4482  Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
4483 
4484  // If we're generating for profiling or coverage, generate a branch to a
4485  // block that increments the RHS counter need to track branch condition
4486  // coverage. In this case, use "FBlock" as both the final "TrueBlock" and
4487  // "FalseBlock" after the increment is done.
4488  if (InstrumentRegions &&
4489  CodeGenFunction::isInstrumentedCondition(E->getRHS())) {
4490  llvm::BasicBlock *FBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.end");
4491  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlockCnt = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.rhscnt");
4492  Builder.CreateCondBr(RHSCond, FBlock, RHSBlockCnt);
4493  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlockCnt);
4494  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E->getRHS());
4495  CGF.EmitBranch(FBlock);
4496  CGF.EmitBlock(FBlock);
4497  }
4498 
4499  // ZExt result to int or bool.
4500  return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(RHSCond, ResTy, "lor.ext");
4501  }
4502 
4503  // 1 || RHS: If it is safe, just elide the RHS, and return 1/true.
4504  if (!CGF.ContainsLabel(E->getRHS()))
4505  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResTy, 1);
4506  }
4507 
4508  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.end");
4509  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.rhs");
4510 
4511  CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation eval(CGF);
4512 
4513  // Branch on the LHS first. If it is true, go to the success (cont) block.
4514  CGF.EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(E->getLHS(), ContBlock, RHSBlock,
4515  CGF.getCurrentProfileCount() -
4516  CGF.getProfileCount(E->getRHS()));
4517 
4518  // Any edges into the ContBlock are now from an (indeterminate number of)
4519  // edges from this first condition. All of these values will be true. Start
4520  // setting up the PHI node in the Cont Block for this.
4521  llvm::PHINode *PN = llvm::PHINode::Create(llvm::Type::getInt1Ty(VMContext), 2,
4522  "", ContBlock);
4523  for (llvm::pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(ContBlock), PE = pred_end(ContBlock);
4524  PI != PE; ++PI)
4525  PN->addIncoming(llvm::ConstantInt::getTrue(VMContext), *PI);
4526 
4527  eval.begin(CGF);
4528 
4529  // Emit the RHS condition as a bool value.
4530  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlock);
4531  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4532  Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
4533 
4534  eval.end(CGF);
4535 
4536  // Reaquire the RHS block, as there may be subblocks inserted.
4537  RHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4538 
4539  // If we're generating for profiling or coverage, generate a branch on the
4540  // RHS to a block that increments the RHS true counter needed to track branch
4541  // condition coverage.
4542  if (InstrumentRegions &&
4543  CodeGenFunction::isInstrumentedCondition(E->getRHS())) {
4544  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlockCnt = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.rhscnt");
4545  Builder.CreateCondBr(RHSCond, ContBlock, RHSBlockCnt);
4546  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlockCnt);
4547  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E->getRHS());
4548  CGF.EmitBranch(ContBlock);
4549  PN->addIncoming(RHSCond, RHSBlockCnt);
4550  }
4551 
4552  // Emit an unconditional branch from this block to ContBlock. Insert an entry
4553  // into the phi node for the edge with the value of RHSCond.
4554  CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
4555  PN->addIncoming(RHSCond, RHSBlock);
4556 
4557  // ZExt result to int.
4558  return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(PN, ResTy, "lor.ext");
4559 }
4560 
4561 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinComma(const BinaryOperator *E) {
4562  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getLHS());
4563  CGF.EnsureInsertPoint();
4564  return Visit(E->getRHS());
4565 }
4566 
4567 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4568 // Other Operators
4569 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4570 
4571 /// isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally - Return true if the specified
4572 /// expression is cheap enough and side-effect-free enough to evaluate
4573 /// unconditionally instead of conditionally. This is used to convert control
4574 /// flow into selects in some cases.
4575 static bool isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally(const Expr *E,
4576  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
4577  // Anything that is an integer or floating point constant is fine.
4578  return E->IgnoreParens()->isEvaluatable(CGF.getContext());
4579 
4580  // Even non-volatile automatic variables can't be evaluated unconditionally.
4581  // Referencing a thread_local may cause non-trivial initialization work to
4582  // occur. If we're inside a lambda and one of the variables is from the scope
4583  // outside the lambda, that function may have returned already. Reading its
4584  // locals is a bad idea. Also, these reads may introduce races there didn't
4585  // exist in the source-level program.
4586 }
4587 
4588 
4589 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::
4590 VisitAbstractConditionalOperator(const AbstractConditionalOperator *E) {
4591  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
4592 
4593  // Bind the common expression if necessary.
4594  CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMapping binding(CGF, E);
4595 
4596  Expr *condExpr = E->getCond();
4597  Expr *lhsExpr = E->getTrueExpr();
4598  Expr *rhsExpr = E->getFalseExpr();
4599 
4600  // If the condition constant folds and can be elided, try to avoid emitting
4601  // the condition and the dead arm.
4602  bool CondExprBool;
4603  if (CGF.ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(condExpr, CondExprBool)) {
4604  Expr *live = lhsExpr, *dead = rhsExpr;
4605  if (!CondExprBool) std::swap(live, dead);
4606 
4607  // If the dead side doesn't have labels we need, just emit the Live part.
4608  if (!CGF.ContainsLabel(dead)) {
4609  if (CondExprBool)
4610  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4611  Value *Result = Visit(live);
4612 
4613  // If the live part is a throw expression, it acts like it has a void
4614  // type, so evaluating it returns a null Value*. However, a conditional
4615  // with non-void type must return a non-null Value*.
4616  if (!Result && !E->getType()->isVoidType())
4617  Result = llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.ConvertType(E->getType()));
4618 
4619  return Result;
4620  }
4621  }
4622 
4623  // OpenCL: If the condition is a vector, we can treat this condition like
4624  // the select function.
4625  if ((CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL && condExpr->getType()->isVectorType()) ||
4626  condExpr->getType()->isExtVectorType()) {
4627  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4628 
4629  llvm::Value *CondV = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(condExpr);
4630  llvm::Value *LHS = Visit(lhsExpr);
4631  llvm::Value *RHS = Visit(rhsExpr);
4632 
4633  llvm::Type *condType = ConvertType(condExpr->getType());
4634  auto *vecTy = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(condType);
4635 
4636  unsigned numElem = vecTy->getNumElements();
4637  llvm::Type *elemType = vecTy->getElementType();
4638 
4639  llvm::Value *zeroVec = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(vecTy);
4640  llvm::Value *TestMSB = Builder.CreateICmpSLT(CondV, zeroVec);
4641  llvm::Value *tmp = Builder.CreateSExt(
4642  TestMSB, llvm::FixedVectorType::get(elemType, numElem), "sext");
4643  llvm::Value *tmp2 = Builder.CreateNot(tmp);
4644 
4645  // Cast float to int to perform ANDs if necessary.
4646  llvm::Value *RHSTmp = RHS;
4647  llvm::Value *LHSTmp = LHS;
4648  bool wasCast = false;
4649  llvm::VectorType *rhsVTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(RHS->getType());
4650  if (rhsVTy->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy()) {
4651  RHSTmp = Builder.CreateBitCast(RHS, tmp2->getType());
4652  LHSTmp = Builder.CreateBitCast(LHS, tmp->getType());
4653  wasCast = true;
4654  }
4655 
4656  llvm::Value *tmp3 = Builder.CreateAnd(RHSTmp, tmp2);
4657  llvm::Value *tmp4 = Builder.CreateAnd(LHSTmp, tmp);
4658  llvm::Value *tmp5 = Builder.CreateOr(tmp3, tmp4, "cond");
4659  if (wasCast)
4660  tmp5 = Builder.CreateBitCast(tmp5, RHS->getType());
4661 
4662  return tmp5;
4663  }
4664 
4665  if (condExpr->getType()->isVectorType()) {
4666  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4667 
4668  llvm::Value *CondV = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(condExpr);
4669  llvm::Value *LHS = Visit(lhsExpr);
4670  llvm::Value *RHS = Visit(rhsExpr);
4671 
4672  llvm::Type *CondType = ConvertType(condExpr->getType());
4673  auto *VecTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(CondType);
4674  llvm::Value *ZeroVec = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(VecTy);
4675 
4676  CondV = Builder.CreateICmpNE(CondV, ZeroVec, "vector_cond");
4677  return Builder.CreateSelect(CondV, LHS, RHS, "vector_select");
4678  }
4679 
4680  // If this is a really simple expression (like x ? 4 : 5), emit this as a
4681  // select instead of as control flow. We can only do this if it is cheap and
4682  // safe to evaluate the LHS and RHS unconditionally.
4683  if (isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally(lhsExpr, CGF) &&
4684  isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally(rhsExpr, CGF)) {
4685  llvm::Value *CondV = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(condExpr);
4686  llvm::Value *StepV = Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(CondV, CGF.Int64Ty);
4687 
4688  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E, StepV);
4689 
4690  llvm::Value *LHS = Visit(lhsExpr);
4691  llvm::Value *RHS = Visit(rhsExpr);
4692  if (!LHS) {
4693  // If the conditional has void type, make sure we return a null Value*.
4694  assert(!RHS && "LHS and RHS types must match");
4695  return nullptr;
4696  }
4697  return Builder.CreateSelect(CondV, LHS, RHS, "cond");
4698  }
4699 
4700  llvm::BasicBlock *LHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.true");
4701  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.false");
4702  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.end");
4703 
4704  CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation eval(CGF);
4705  CGF.EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(condExpr, LHSBlock, RHSBlock,
4706  CGF.getProfileCount(lhsExpr));
4707 
4708  CGF.EmitBlock(LHSBlock);
4709  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4710  eval.begin(CGF);
4711  Value *LHS = Visit(lhsExpr);
4712  eval.end(CGF);
4713 
4714  LHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4715  Builder.CreateBr(ContBlock);
4716 
4717  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlock);
4718  eval.begin(CGF);
4719  Value *RHS = Visit(rhsExpr);
4720  eval.end(CGF);
4721 
4722  RHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4723  CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
4724 
4725  // If the LHS or RHS is a throw expression, it will be legitimately null.
4726  if (!LHS)
4727  return RHS;
4728  if (!RHS)
4729  return LHS;
4730 
4731  // Create a PHI node for the real part.
4732  llvm::PHINode *PN = Builder.CreatePHI(LHS->getType(), 2, "cond");
4733  PN->addIncoming(LHS, LHSBlock);
4734  PN->addIncoming(RHS, RHSBlock);
4735  return PN;
4736 }

4739  return Visit(E->getChosenSubExpr());
4740 }

4742 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitVAArgExpr(VAArgExpr *VE) {
4743  QualType Ty = VE->getType();
4744 
4745  if (Ty->isVariablyModifiedType())
4746  CGF.EmitVariablyModifiedType(Ty);
4747 
4748  Address ArgValue = Address::invalid();
4749  Address ArgPtr = CGF.EmitVAArg(VE, ArgValue);
4750 
4751  llvm::Type *ArgTy = ConvertType(VE->getType());
4752 
4753  // If EmitVAArg fails, emit an error.
4754  if (!ArgPtr.isValid()) {
4755  CGF.ErrorUnsupported(VE, "va_arg expression");
4756  return llvm::UndefValue::get(ArgTy);
4757  }
4758 
4759  // FIXME Volatility.
4760  llvm::Value *Val = Builder.CreateLoad(ArgPtr);
4761 
4762  // If EmitVAArg promoted the type, we must truncate it.
4763  if (ArgTy != Val->getType()) {
4764  if (ArgTy->isPointerTy() && !Val->getType()->isPointerTy())
4765  Val = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Val, ArgTy);
4766  else
4767  Val = Builder.CreateTrunc(Val, ArgTy);
4768  }
4769 
4770  return Val;
4771 }

4777 // Convert a vec3 to vec4, or vice versa.
4778 static Value *ConvertVec3AndVec4(CGBuilderTy &Builder, CodeGenFunction &CGF,
4779  Value *Src, unsigned NumElementsDst) {
4780  static constexpr int Mask[] = {0, 1, 2, -1};
4781  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Src,
4782  llvm::makeArrayRef(Mask, NumElementsDst));
4783 }
4784 
4785 // Create cast instructions for converting LLVM value \p Src to LLVM type \p
4786 // DstTy. \p Src has the same size as \p DstTy. Both are single value types
4787 // but could be scalar or vectors of different lengths, and either can be
4788 // pointer.
4789 // There are 4 cases:
4790 // 1. non-pointer -> non-pointer : needs 1 bitcast
4791 // 2. pointer -> pointer : needs 1 bitcast or addrspacecast
4792 // 3. pointer -> non-pointer
4793 // a) pointer -> intptr_t : needs 1 ptrtoint
4794 // b) pointer -> non-intptr_t : needs 1 ptrtoint then 1 bitcast
4795 // 4. non-pointer -> pointer
4796 // a) intptr_t -> pointer : needs 1 inttoptr
4797 // b) non-intptr_t -> pointer : needs 1 bitcast then 1 inttoptr
4798 // Note: for cases 3b and 4b two casts are required since LLVM casts do not
4799 // allow casting directly between pointer types and non-integer non-pointer
4800 // types.
4801 static Value *createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(CGBuilderTy &Builder,
4802  const llvm::DataLayout &DL,
4803  Value *Src, llvm::Type *DstTy,
4804  StringRef Name = "") {
4805  auto SrcTy = Src->getType();
4806 
4807  // Case 1.
4808  if (!SrcTy->isPointerTy() && !DstTy->isPointerTy())
4809  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DstTy, Name);
4810 
4811  // Case 2.
4812  if (SrcTy->isPointerTy() && DstTy->isPointerTy())
4813  return Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Src, DstTy, Name);
4814 
4815  // Case 3.
4816  if (SrcTy->isPointerTy() && !DstTy->isPointerTy()) {
4817  // Case 3b.
4818  if (!DstTy->isIntegerTy())
4819  Src = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Src, DL.getIntPtrType(SrcTy));
4820  // Cases 3a and 3b.
4821  return Builder.CreateBitOrPointerCast(Src, DstTy, Name);
4822  }
4823 
4824  // Case 4b.
4825  if (!SrcTy->isIntegerTy())
4826  Src = Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DL.getIntPtrType(DstTy));
4827  // Cases 4a and 4b.
4828  return Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Src, DstTy, Name);
4829 }
4830 
4831 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitAsTypeExpr(AsTypeExpr *E) {
4832  Value *Src = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getSrcExpr());
4833  llvm::Type *DstTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
4834 
4835  llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
4836  unsigned NumElementsSrc =
4837  isa<llvm::VectorType>(SrcTy)
4838  ? cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(SrcTy)->getNumElements()
4839  : 0;
4840  unsigned NumElementsDst =
4841  isa<llvm::VectorType>(DstTy)
4842  ? cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(DstTy)->getNumElements()
4843  : 0;
4844 
4845  // Use bit vector expansion for ext_vector_type boolean vectors.
4846  if (E->getType()->isExtVectorBoolType())
4847  return CGF.emitBoolVecConversion(Src, NumElementsDst, "astype");
4848 
4849  // Going from vec3 to non-vec3 is a special case and requires a shuffle
4850  // vector to get a vec4, then a bitcast if the target type is different.
4851  if (NumElementsSrc == 3 && NumElementsDst != 3) {
4852  Src = ConvertVec3AndVec4(Builder, CGF, Src, 4);
4853  Src = createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(Builder, CGF.CGM.getDataLayout(), Src,
4854  DstTy);
4855 
4856  Src->setName("astype");
4857  return Src;
4858  }
4859 
4860  // Going from non-vec3 to vec3 is a special case and requires a bitcast
4861  // to vec4 if the original type is not vec4, then a shuffle vector to
4862  // get a vec3.
4863  if (NumElementsSrc != 3 && NumElementsDst == 3) {
4864  auto *Vec4Ty = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
4865  cast<llvm::VectorType>(DstTy)->getElementType(), 4);
4866  Src = createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(Builder, CGF.CGM.getDataLayout(), Src,
4867  Vec4Ty);
4868 
4869  Src = ConvertVec3AndVec4(Builder, CGF, Src, 3);
4870  Src->setName("astype");
4871  return Src;
4872  }
4873 
4874  return createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(Builder, CGF.CGM.getDataLayout(),
4875  Src, DstTy, "astype");
4876 }
