4995 struct GEPOffsetAndOverflow {
4996  // The total (signed) byte offset for the GEP.
4997  llvm::Value *TotalOffset;
4998  // The offset overflow flag - true if the total offset overflows.
4999  llvm::Value *OffsetOverflows;
5000 };
5001 
5002 /// Evaluate given GEPVal, which is either an inbounds GEP, or a constant,
5003 /// and compute the total offset it applies from it's base pointer BasePtr.
5004 /// Returns offset in bytes and a boolean flag whether an overflow happened
5005 /// during evaluation.
5006 static GEPOffsetAndOverflow EmitGEPOffsetInBytes(Value *BasePtr, Value *GEPVal,
5007  llvm::LLVMContext &VMContext,
5008  CodeGenModule &CGM,
5009  CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
5010  const auto &DL = CGM.getDataLayout();
5011 
5012  // The total (signed) byte offset for the GEP.
5013  llvm::Value *TotalOffset = nullptr;
5014 
5015  // Was the GEP already reduced to a constant?
5016  if (isa<llvm::Constant>(GEPVal)) {
5017  // Compute the offset by casting both pointers to integers and subtracting:
5018  // GEPVal = BasePtr + ptr(Offset) <--> Offset = int(GEPVal) - int(BasePtr)
5019  Value *BasePtr_int =
5020  Builder.CreatePtrToInt(BasePtr, DL.getIntPtrType(BasePtr->getType()));
5021  Value *GEPVal_int =
5022  Builder.CreatePtrToInt(GEPVal, DL.getIntPtrType(GEPVal->getType()));
5023  TotalOffset = Builder.CreateSub(GEPVal_int, BasePtr_int);
5024  return {TotalOffset, /*OffsetOverflows=*/Builder.getFalse()};
5025  }
5026 
5027  auto *GEP = cast<llvm::GEPOperator>(GEPVal);
5028  assert(GEP->getPointerOperand() == BasePtr &&
5029  "BasePtr must be the base of the GEP.");
5030  assert(GEP->isInBounds() && "Expected inbounds GEP");
5031 
5032  auto *IntPtrTy = DL.getIntPtrType(GEP->getPointerOperandType());
5033 
5034  // Grab references to the signed add/mul overflow intrinsics for intptr_t.
5035  auto *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::getNullValue(IntPtrTy);
5036  auto *SAddIntrinsic =
5037  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow, IntPtrTy);
5038  auto *SMulIntrinsic =
5039  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow, IntPtrTy);
5040 
5041  // The offset overflow flag - true if the total offset overflows.
5042  llvm::Value *OffsetOverflows = Builder.getFalse();
5043 
5044  /// Return the result of the given binary operation.
5045  auto eval = [&](BinaryOperator::Opcode Opcode, llvm::Value *LHS,
5046  llvm::Value *RHS) -> llvm::Value * {
5047  assert((Opcode == BO_Add || Opcode == BO_Mul) && "Can't eval binop");
5048 
5049  // If the operands are constants, return a constant result.
5050  if (auto *LHSCI = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(LHS)) {
5051  if (auto *RHSCI = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(RHS)) {
5052  llvm::APInt N;
5053  bool HasOverflow = mayHaveIntegerOverflow(LHSCI, RHSCI, Opcode,
5054  /*Signed=*/true, N);
5055  if (HasOverflow)
5056  OffsetOverflows = Builder.getTrue();
5057  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(VMContext, N);
5058  }
5059  }
5060 
5061  // Otherwise, compute the result with checked arithmetic.
5062  auto *ResultAndOverflow = Builder.CreateCall(
5063  (Opcode == BO_Add) ? SAddIntrinsic : SMulIntrinsic, {LHS, RHS});
5064  OffsetOverflows = Builder.CreateOr(
5065  Builder.CreateExtractValue(ResultAndOverflow, 1), OffsetOverflows);
5066  return Builder.CreateExtractValue(ResultAndOverflow, 0);
5067  };
5068 
5069  // Determine the total byte offset by looking at each GEP operand.
5070  for (auto GTI = llvm::gep_type_begin(GEP), GTE = llvm::gep_type_end(GEP);
5071  GTI != GTE; ++GTI) {
5072  llvm::Value *LocalOffset;
5073  auto *Index = GTI.getOperand();
5074  // Compute the local offset contributed by this indexing step:
5075  if (auto *STy = GTI.getStructTypeOrNull()) {
5076  // For struct indexing, the local offset is the byte position of the
5077  // specified field.
5078  unsigned FieldNo = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Index)->getZExtValue();
5079  LocalOffset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
5080  IntPtrTy, DL.getStructLayout(STy)->getElementOffset(FieldNo));
5081  } else {
5082  // Otherwise this is array-like indexing. The local offset is the index
5083  // multiplied by the element size.
5084  auto *ElementSize = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
5085  IntPtrTy, DL.getTypeAllocSize(GTI.getIndexedType()));
5086  auto *IndexS = Builder.CreateIntCast(Index, IntPtrTy, /*isSigned=*/true);
5087  LocalOffset = eval(BO_Mul, ElementSize, IndexS);
5088  }
5089 
5090  // If this is the first offset, set it as the total offset. Otherwise, add
5091  // the local offset into the running total.
5092  if (!TotalOffset || TotalOffset == Zero)
5093  TotalOffset = LocalOffset;
5094  else
5095  TotalOffset = eval(BO_Add, TotalOffset, LocalOffset);
5096  }
5097 
5098  return {TotalOffset, OffsetOverflows};
5099 }
5100 
5101 Value *
5102 CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(llvm::Type *ElemTy, Value *Ptr,
5103  ArrayRef<Value *> IdxList,
5104  bool SignedIndices, bool IsSubtraction,
5105  SourceLocation Loc, const Twine &Name) {
5106  llvm::Type *PtrTy = Ptr->getType();
5107  Value *GEPVal = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(ElemTy, Ptr, IdxList, Name);
5108 
5109  // If the pointer overflow sanitizer isn't enabled, do nothing.
5110  if (!SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::PointerOverflow))
5111  return GEPVal;
5112 
5113  // Perform nullptr-and-offset check unless the nullptr is defined.
5114  bool PerformNullCheck = !NullPointerIsDefined(
5115  Builder.GetInsertBlock()->getParent(), PtrTy->getPointerAddressSpace());
5116  // Check for overflows unless the GEP got constant-folded,
5117  // and only in the default address space
5118  bool PerformOverflowCheck =
5119  !isa<llvm::Constant>(GEPVal) && PtrTy->getPointerAddressSpace() == 0;
5120 
5121  if (!(PerformNullCheck || PerformOverflowCheck))
5122  return GEPVal;
5123 
5124  const auto &DL = CGM.getDataLayout();
5125 
5126  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
5127  llvm::Type *IntPtrTy = DL.getIntPtrType(PtrTy);
5128 
5129  GEPOffsetAndOverflow EvaluatedGEP =
5130  EmitGEPOffsetInBytes(Ptr, GEPVal, getLLVMContext(), CGM, Builder);
5131 
5132  assert((!isa<llvm::Constant>(EvaluatedGEP.TotalOffset) ||
5133  EvaluatedGEP.OffsetOverflows == Builder.getFalse()) &&
5134  "If the offset got constant-folded, we don't expect that there was an "
5135  "overflow.");
5136 
5137  auto *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::getNullValue(IntPtrTy);
5138 
5139  // Common case: if the total offset is zero, and we are using C++ semantics,
5140  // where nullptr+0 is defined, don't emit a check.
5141  if (EvaluatedGEP.TotalOffset == Zero && CGM.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
5142  return GEPVal;
5143 
5144  // Now that we've computed the total offset, add it to the base pointer (with
5145  // wrapping semantics).
5146  auto *IntPtr = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Ptr, IntPtrTy);
5147  auto *ComputedGEP = Builder.CreateAdd(IntPtr, EvaluatedGEP.TotalOffset);
5148 
5149  llvm::SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 2> Checks;
5150 
5151  if (PerformNullCheck) {
5152  // In C++, if the base pointer evaluates to a null pointer value,
5153  // the only valid pointer this inbounds GEP can produce is also
5154  // a null pointer, so the offset must also evaluate to zero.
5155  // Likewise, if we have non-zero base pointer, we can not get null pointer
5156  // as a result, so the offset can not be -intptr_t(BasePtr).
5157  // In other words, both pointers are either null, or both are non-null,
5158  // or the behaviour is undefined.
5159  //
5160  // C, however, is more strict in this regard, and gives more
5161  // optimization opportunities: in C, additionally, nullptr+0 is undefined.
5162  // So both the input to the 'gep inbounds' AND the output must not be null.
5163  auto *BaseIsNotNullptr = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Ptr);
5164  auto *ResultIsNotNullptr = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(ComputedGEP);
5165  auto *Valid =
5166  CGM.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus
5167  ? Builder.CreateICmpEQ(BaseIsNotNullptr, ResultIsNotNullptr)
5168  : Builder.CreateAnd(BaseIsNotNullptr, ResultIsNotNullptr);
5169  Checks.emplace_back(Valid, SanitizerKind::PointerOverflow);
5170  }
5171 
5172  if (PerformOverflowCheck) {
5173  // The GEP is valid if:
5174  // 1) The total offset doesn't overflow, and
5175  // 2) The sign of the difference between the computed address and the base
5176  // pointer matches the sign of the total offset.
5177  llvm::Value *ValidGEP;
5178  auto *NoOffsetOverflow = Builder.CreateNot(EvaluatedGEP.OffsetOverflows);
5179  if (SignedIndices) {
5180  // GEP is computed as `unsigned base + signed offset`, therefore:
5181  // * If offset was positive, then the computed pointer can not be
5182  // [unsigned] less than the base pointer, unless it overflowed.
5183  // * If offset was negative, then the computed pointer can not be
5184  // [unsigned] greater than the bas pointere, unless it overflowed.
5185  auto *PosOrZeroValid = Builder.CreateICmpUGE(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5186  auto *PosOrZeroOffset =
5187  Builder.CreateICmpSGE(EvaluatedGEP.TotalOffset, Zero);
5188  llvm::Value *NegValid = Builder.CreateICmpULT(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5189  ValidGEP =
5190  Builder.CreateSelect(PosOrZeroOffset, PosOrZeroValid, NegValid);
5191  } else if (!IsSubtraction) {
5192  // GEP is computed as `unsigned base + unsigned offset`, therefore the
5193  // computed pointer can not be [unsigned] less than base pointer,
5194  // unless there was an overflow.
5195  // Equivalent to `@llvm.uadd.with.overflow(%base, %offset)`.
5196  ValidGEP = Builder.CreateICmpUGE(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5197  } else {
5198  // GEP is computed as `unsigned base - unsigned offset`, therefore the
5199  // computed pointer can not be [unsigned] greater than base pointer,
5200  // unless there was an overflow.
5201  // Equivalent to `@llvm.usub.with.overflow(%base, sub(0, %offset))`.
5202  ValidGEP = Builder.CreateICmpULE(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5203  }
5204  ValidGEP = Builder.CreateAnd(ValidGEP, NoOffsetOverflow);
5205  Checks.emplace_back(ValidGEP, SanitizerKind::PointerOverflow);
5206  }
5207 
5208  assert(!Checks.empty() && "Should have produced some checks.");
5209 
5210  llvm::Constant *StaticArgs[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc)};
5211  // Pass the computed GEP to the runtime to avoid emitting poisoned arguments.
5212  llvm::Value *DynamicArgs[] = {IntPtr, ComputedGEP};
5213  EmitCheck(Checks, SanitizerHandler::PointerOverflow, StaticArgs, DynamicArgs);
5214 
5215  return GEPVal;
5216 }
